1
00:00:09,113 --> 00:00:10,530
- BUT, YOU KNOW, ROSIE,
SHE SAY TO ME,

2
00:00:10,530 --> 00:00:14,534
"LESTER, THIS LADY FROM AMERICA,
SHE’S IN A BIG HURRY,

3
00:00:14,534 --> 00:00:15,827
"AND SHE NEED TO GO PLACES,

4
00:00:15,827 --> 00:00:18,705
AND YOU, LESTER, ARE THE
BEST PERSON TO TAKE THE LADY,"

5
00:00:18,705 --> 00:00:24,003
SO I GIVE UP ALL MY OTHER JOBS,
AND I TAKE YOU TO SEE MR. VARTY.

6
00:00:53,615 --> 00:00:54,824
- HOW FAR IS IT?

7
00:00:54,824 --> 00:00:57,203
- NOT SO FAR.

8
00:01:22,769 --> 00:01:24,271
HEY.

9
00:01:24,271 --> 00:01:25,022
UGH.

10
00:01:25,022 --> 00:01:25,772
- WHAT’S WRONG.

11
00:01:25,772 --> 00:01:27,274
- [muttering]
WHAT A BOMB!

12
00:01:27,274 --> 00:01:29,318
- TELL ME, WHAT IS IT?

13
00:01:29,318 --> 00:01:32,113
- [muttering]

14
00:01:32,113 --> 00:01:35,615
- [groans]
I CAN’T BELIEVE THIS.

15
00:01:35,615 --> 00:01:36,283
boom!

16
00:01:36,283 --> 00:01:38,244
WHAT AM I DOING HERE?

17
00:02:23,873 --> 00:02:27,042
- MISS CHRISTINE!

18
00:02:27,042 --> 00:02:28,043
HEY!

19
00:02:28,043 --> 00:02:29,879
MISS CHRISTINE!

20
00:02:29,879 --> 00:02:31,547
IT’S THAT WAY.

21
00:02:31,547 --> 00:02:33,715
I THINK.

22
00:02:33,715 --> 00:02:34,884
- YOU THINK?

23
00:02:34,884 --> 00:02:36,468
- YEAH.

24
00:02:52,026 --> 00:02:54,653
WE’RE HERE.

25
00:02:54,653 --> 00:02:58,823
- THIS IS IT?

26
00:02:58,823 --> 00:03:01,076
MR. VARTY?

27
00:03:01,076 --> 00:03:02,369
- HEY, I MUST GO NOW.

28
00:03:02,369 --> 00:03:04,371
- OH, OKAY.
ALL RIGHT.

29
00:03:04,371 --> 00:03:04,914
YEAH.

30
00:03:04,914 --> 00:03:06,665
HEY, THANKS A LOT, LESTER.
- OH, YEAH.

31
00:03:06,665 --> 00:03:08,209
- THANKS A LOT, REALLY.
- OKAY.

32
00:03:08,209 --> 00:03:13,088
SEE YOU LATER.
OKAY, BYE, MISS CHRISTINE.

33
00:03:13,088 --> 00:03:16,300
- BYE, LESTER.

34
00:03:28,853 --> 00:03:31,273
MR. VARTY!

35
00:03:31,273 --> 00:03:33,609
HELLO!

36
00:03:37,737 --> 00:03:40,699
I COULD HARDLY BELIEVE
I WAS FINALLY HERE,

37
00:03:40,699 --> 00:03:43,494
IN A PLACE BEYOND IMAGINATION,

38
00:03:43,494 --> 00:03:49,124
ITS BEAUTY SO UNTAMED,
IT FILLED ME WITH UNCERTAINTY

39
00:03:49,124 --> 00:03:53,295
BUT ALSO WITH
A WONDERFUL NEW HOPE.

40
00:04:23,325 --> 00:04:24,326
OH!

41
00:04:24,326 --> 00:04:25,369
MR. VARTY.

42
00:04:25,369 --> 00:04:27,246
- OH, MR. JOHN PASSED EARLY.

43
00:04:27,246 --> 00:04:27,997
I’M ELMON.

44
00:04:27,997 --> 00:04:29,707
- OH, HI.
I’M CHRISTINE SHAYE.

45
00:04:29,707 --> 00:04:31,959
NICE TO MEET YOU.
- HI, NICE TO MEET YOU.

46
00:04:31,959 --> 00:04:32,792
- UH, EXCUSE ME.

47
00:04:32,792 --> 00:04:34,086
I SORT OF MADE
MYSELF AT HOME HERE.

48
00:04:34,086 --> 00:04:36,547
I DIDN’T KNOW WHEN YOU WERE
COMING BACK, SO...

49
00:04:36,547 --> 00:04:38,257
- OKAY.
- THANK YOU.

50
00:04:38,257 --> 00:04:39,258
- PLEASURE.

51
00:04:39,258 --> 00:04:39,925
- MR. VARTY.

52
00:04:39,925 --> 00:04:41,385
HI, IT’S A PLEASURE TO MEET YOU.

53
00:04:41,385 --> 00:04:43,012
I’M CHRISTINE SHAYE.

54
00:04:43,012 --> 00:04:44,680
- HI, CALL ME J.V.

55
00:04:44,680 --> 00:04:46,390
- J.V.

56
00:04:46,390 --> 00:04:47,474
YOU DID GET MY FAX, DIDN’T YOU,

57
00:04:47,474 --> 00:04:49,809
THAT I WAS COMING
ABOUT THE PROGRAM?

58
00:04:49,809 --> 00:04:50,728
- AH, YEAH.

59
00:04:50,728 --> 00:04:52,688
DIDN’T REALIZE IT WAS SO SOON.

60
00:04:52,688 --> 00:04:54,106
- OH, WELL...

61
00:04:54,106 --> 00:04:56,400
I HOPE YOU DON’T MIND
I MADE MYSELF AT HOME.

62
00:04:56,400 --> 00:04:58,319
THESE ARE WONDERFUL PICTURES
OF THE LEOPARDS.

63
00:04:58,319 --> 00:05:01,739
- YEAH, THIS IS THE MOTHER WE’VE
BEEN FOLLOWING FOR 12 YEARS.

64
00:05:01,739 --> 00:05:03,032
- OH, THEY’RE GORGEOUS.

65
00:05:03,032 --> 00:05:04,241
- WANT SOME TEA?

66
00:05:04,241 --> 00:05:06,660
- TEA WOULD BE GREAT.
THANK YOU.

67
00:05:06,660 --> 00:05:08,746
UM, STRONG, NO MILK, TWO SUGARS.

68
00:05:08,746 --> 00:05:09,788
- OKAY, WE’LL HAVE A TEA.

69
00:05:09,788 --> 00:05:13,083
- TAKE A SEAT.
MAKE YOURSELF AT HOME.

70
00:05:13,083 --> 00:05:14,460
- THANK YOU.

71
00:05:14,460 --> 00:05:16,295
IT CERTAINLY IS SOME PLACE
YOU’VE GOT HERE.

72
00:05:16,295 --> 00:05:18,255
IT’S NOT EXACTLY WHAT
I’D IMAGINED.

73
00:05:18,255 --> 00:05:19,423
- SO DID YOU HAVE A GOOD TRIP?

74
00:05:19,423 --> 00:05:21,884
- WELL, IT’S BEEN QUITE
AN EXPERIENCE.

75
00:05:21,884 --> 00:05:25,637
TOOK A LITTLE LONGER
THAN I EXPECTED.

76
00:05:25,637 --> 00:05:28,140
YOU KNOW, I’VE SEEN
MANY OF YOUR FILMS.

77
00:05:28,140 --> 00:05:29,767
THEY’RE REALLY GREAT.

78
00:05:29,767 --> 00:05:31,352
REALLY SPECIAL.

79
00:05:31,352 --> 00:05:32,227
- TEA FOR YOU.

80
00:05:32,227 --> 00:05:34,021
- THANK YOU.
- PLEASURE.

81
00:05:34,021 --> 00:05:36,440
- THANK YOU.

82
00:05:36,440 --> 00:05:40,152
MM. SOME KIND OF HERBAL TEA,
HUH?

83
00:05:40,152 --> 00:05:41,195
MR. VARTY--J.V.--

84
00:05:41,195 --> 00:05:45,157
I WOULD LIKE YOU TO HELP ME
MAKE A FILM ABOUT AFRICA.

85
00:05:45,157 --> 00:05:47,034
I FIGURE, WITH YOUR KNOWLEDGE
OF AFRICA,

86
00:05:47,034 --> 00:05:48,619
YOU’D BE THE BEST PERSON
TO HELP.

87
00:05:48,619 --> 00:05:50,829
DID YOU SEEOUT OF AFRICA?

88
00:05:50,829 --> 00:05:51,997
- MM-MM.

89
00:05:51,997 --> 00:05:53,123
- WELL, ANYWAY,

90
00:05:53,123 --> 00:05:57,753
I WANT OUR PROGRAM
TO BE A BIT LIKE THAT.

91
00:05:57,753 --> 00:06:00,631
A ROMANCE WITH AFRICA,

92
00:06:00,631 --> 00:06:01,507
THE MYSTICAL CONTINENT.

93
00:06:01,507 --> 00:06:03,175
- YOU KNOW THEY’RE MAKING
PRETTY PICTURES

94
00:06:03,175 --> 00:06:06,387
ABOUT THE ROMANCE OF AFRICA
ALL THE TIME.

95
00:06:06,387 --> 00:06:09,139
I CAN’T HELP YOU WITH THAT.

96
00:06:09,139 --> 00:06:11,392
YOU WANT TO MAKE
THE REAL ISSUES,

97
00:06:11,392 --> 00:06:13,018
THAT’S ANOTHER STORY.

98
00:06:13,018 --> 00:06:15,187
- [tsking]
J.V.

99
00:06:15,187 --> 00:06:17,981
[speaking African language]

100
00:06:20,818 --> 00:06:23,153
- I DON’T KNOW WHAT--
WHAT’D HE SAY?

101
00:06:23,153 --> 00:06:28,575
- UH, HE SAYS,
"HOW’S THE TEA?"

102
00:06:28,575 --> 00:06:29,743
- ALL THAT TO SAY THAT, HUH?

103
00:06:29,743 --> 00:06:30,911
IT’S GREAT.
THANK YOU.

104
00:06:30,911 --> 00:06:32,913
LOOK, WHY DON’T YOU JUST TAKE
A LOOK AT THE SCRIPT.

105
00:06:32,913 --> 00:06:35,124
I’M SURE YOU’LL HAVE
SOME IDEAS--

106
00:06:35,124 --> 00:06:35,875
[animal roaring]

107
00:06:35,875 --> 00:06:39,503
[both speaking African language]

108
00:06:41,213 --> 00:06:43,006
- COME ON.
WE’VE GOT TO CHECK IT OUT.

109
00:06:43,006 --> 00:06:44,591
- YOU WANT ME TO COME?
WANT ME TO COME?

110
00:06:44,591 --> 00:06:46,135
- YEAH, YEAH!
LET’S GO!

111
00:06:46,135 --> 00:06:46,802
- ALL RIGHT.

112
00:06:46,802 --> 00:06:48,929
- TAKE THIS.
WHITE’S TOO BRIGHT.

113
00:06:48,929 --> 00:06:49,513
- OKAY.

114
00:06:49,513 --> 00:06:51,891
- [speaking African language]

115
00:07:00,441 --> 00:07:04,278
[speaking African language]

116
00:07:06,196 --> 00:07:09,032
[animal roaring]

117
00:07:09,032 --> 00:07:10,742
- WHAT WAS THAT?

118
00:07:11,743 --> 00:07:13,245
- SOUNDS LIKE LEOPARDS FIGHTING.

119
00:07:13,245 --> 00:07:14,997
[speaking African language]

120
00:07:14,997 --> 00:07:18,292
- [speaking African language]

121
00:07:18,292 --> 00:07:20,879
- LET’S GO.

122
00:07:20,879 --> 00:07:23,172
[engine turns over]

123
00:07:50,073 --> 00:07:52,952
- [speaking African language]

124
00:07:52,952 --> 00:07:57,080
- YEAH.
- IT’S THE MOTHER LEOPARD.

125
00:07:57,080 --> 00:08:00,919
[speaking African language]

126
00:08:03,253 --> 00:08:06,883
[leopard rumbling]

127
00:08:07,424 --> 00:08:10,469
[speaking African language]

128
00:08:10,469 --> 00:08:11,595
- CAN’T WE DO SOMETHING?

129
00:08:11,595 --> 00:08:13,973
- NAH.
CAN’T INTERFERE.

130
00:08:15,182 --> 00:08:18,895
[roaring and snarling]

131
00:08:20,897 --> 00:08:21,981
- WHY ARE THEY FIGHTING?

132
00:08:21,981 --> 00:08:24,816
- THIS LEOPARD HERE HAS INVADED
THE MOTHER’S TERRITORY.

133
00:08:24,816 --> 00:08:26,818
[speaking African language]

134
00:08:26,818 --> 00:08:27,653
SHE’S INJURED.

135
00:08:27,653 --> 00:08:29,738
- J.V.
[speaking African language]

136
00:08:29,738 --> 00:08:33,450
[roaring and snarling]

137
00:08:48,131 --> 00:08:49,174
[speaking African language]

138
00:08:49,174 --> 00:08:53,972
- IT’S ONE OF THE WORST
TERRITORIAL FIGHTS I’VE SEEN.

139
00:08:53,972 --> 00:08:55,847
- SHE GONNA BE OKAY?

140
00:08:55,847 --> 00:08:57,474
- YEAH, I THINK SO.

141
00:08:57,474 --> 00:09:00,185
I THINK SHE’S OKAY.

142
00:09:13,657 --> 00:09:17,286
[insects buzzing]

143
00:09:25,127 --> 00:09:27,880
- J.V.

144
00:09:27,880 --> 00:09:29,966
I WAS THINKING ABOUT THE FILM.

145
00:09:29,966 --> 00:09:33,635
J.V, ARE YOU AWAKE?

146
00:09:53,739 --> 00:09:59,703
- THIS IS A DEN THAT
SHE’S USED ABOUT FIVE WEEKS AGO.

147
00:09:59,703 --> 00:10:01,288
BUT IT LOOKS LIKE SHE’S LEFT.

148
00:10:01,288 --> 00:10:02,414
[speaks African language]

149
00:10:02,414 --> 00:10:05,292
- [speaking African language]

150
00:10:11,465 --> 00:10:15,594
- J.V.
[speaking African language]

151
00:10:15,594 --> 00:10:18,056
- LION.

152
00:10:27,899 --> 00:10:31,234
WELL, THIS IS ABOUT AS BIG
AS YOU’LL SEE IN AFRICA.

153
00:10:31,234 --> 00:10:32,402
- WOW.
AMAZING.

154
00:10:32,402 --> 00:10:36,239
- THESE ARE THE TWO
DOMINANT MALES OF THE AREA.

155
00:10:36,239 --> 00:10:38,533
- MAGNIFICENT.

156
00:10:38,533 --> 00:10:39,326
- J.V.,
J.V.

157
00:10:39,326 --> 00:10:41,996
[speaking African language]

158
00:10:41,996 --> 00:10:44,790
- HEY, LET’S GO FIND THE CUBS.

159
00:11:00,722 --> 00:11:04,351
[birds twittering]

160
00:11:20,492 --> 00:11:23,996
[Jeep rumbling]

161
00:11:25,247 --> 00:11:28,126
- [speaking African language]

162
00:11:34,381 --> 00:11:37,135
- THEY’RE ADORABLE.

163
00:11:41,513 --> 00:11:47,145
I HAD NO IDEA
THEY WERE THIS BEAUTIFUL.

164
00:11:47,145 --> 00:11:48,104
HOW OLD ARE THEY?

165
00:11:48,104 --> 00:11:51,398
- I COUNT AROUND SIX WEEKS NOW.

166
00:11:53,067 --> 00:11:54,359
- WHERE’S THE MOTHER?

167
00:11:54,359 --> 00:11:56,112
- SHE’D BE OUT HUNTING.

168
00:11:56,112 --> 00:11:57,571
SHE LEAVES THEM
FOR A DAY OR TWO.

169
00:11:57,571 --> 00:12:00,240
DEPENDS HOW SOON
SHE CAN GET SOME FOOD.

170
00:12:00,240 --> 00:12:01,408
- AND THEY DON’T RUN AWAY?

171
00:12:01,408 --> 00:12:03,827
- NO.
STAY HERE IN THE ROCKS.

172
00:12:03,827 --> 00:12:06,747
SEE THE ONE SLIGHTLY BIGGER?

173
00:12:06,747 --> 00:12:09,499
IT’S A LITTLE MALE.

174
00:12:11,127 --> 00:12:14,337
IT’S A BIT BOLDER AS WELL.

175
00:12:29,728 --> 00:12:31,898
WE CAN’T STAY HERE TOO LONG.

176
00:12:31,898 --> 00:12:35,109
I DON’T WANT THE MOTHER
TO CATCH US HERE AT THE DEN.

177
00:12:35,109 --> 00:12:39,030
ANYWAY, I GOT SOMETHING ELSE
TO SHOW YOU.

178
00:13:01,426 --> 00:13:05,305
[projector clatters and hums]

179
00:13:10,186 --> 00:13:13,647
WELL, THIS IS THE MOTHER
THAT WE FOLLOWED FOR 12 YEARS.

180
00:13:13,647 --> 00:13:14,606
WHEN WE FIRST SAW HER,

181
00:13:14,606 --> 00:13:19,444
SHE WAS ELUSIVE, AGGRESSIVE,
AND VERY DIFFICULT TO FOLLOW,

182
00:13:19,444 --> 00:13:25,201
JUST LIKE ANY OTHER
WILD LEOPARD.

183
00:13:25,201 --> 00:13:26,827
THEN GRADUALLY, SHE RELAXED,

184
00:13:26,827 --> 00:13:30,705
ALLOWING US
INTO HER PRIVATE WORLD.

185
00:13:30,705 --> 00:13:32,457
SHE’S A VERY SUCCESSFUL MOTHER,

186
00:13:32,457 --> 00:13:35,920
AND HAS ALLOWED US TO FILM
NO LESS THAN NINE

187
00:13:35,920 --> 00:13:37,046
OF HER LITTERS OF CUBS.

188
00:13:37,046 --> 00:13:40,091
NO OTHER HUMAN BEING HAS HAD
SUCH A CLOSE RELATIONSHIP

189
00:13:40,091 --> 00:13:42,093
WITH A WILD LEOPARD BEFORE.

190
00:13:42,093 --> 00:13:46,138
WELL, THIS IS HER MOVING ONE OF
THE FIFTH LITTER TO ANOTHER DEN,

191
00:13:46,138 --> 00:13:47,722
WHICH SHE DOES EVERY FEW DAYS

192
00:13:47,722 --> 00:13:50,392
TO LESSEN THE CHANCES
OF LION AND HYENA

193
00:13:50,392 --> 00:13:52,144
FINDING AND KILLING THEM.

194
00:13:52,144 --> 00:13:54,437
WELL, HERE YOU SEE
SARCOPTIC MANGE,

195
00:13:54,437 --> 00:13:56,356
WHICH LEOPARDS
SOMETIMES CONTRACT.

196
00:13:56,356 --> 00:14:00,278
IT’S TINY PARASITE WHICH ATTACKS
THE SKIN AND THE FUR

197
00:14:00,278 --> 00:14:02,487
AND MOST OFTEN RESULTS IN DEATH.

198
00:14:02,487 --> 00:14:04,866
ALL PREDATORS ARE COMPETING
FOR FOOD AND SPACE

199
00:14:04,866 --> 00:14:08,451
AND WILL IMMEDIATELY KILL
THE CUBS OF ANOTHER PREDATOR

200
00:14:08,451 --> 00:14:09,703
IF THEY FIND THEM.

201
00:14:09,703 --> 00:14:12,455
THIS IS THE SADDEST MOMENT
WE EVER SHARED WITH HER.

202
00:14:12,455 --> 00:14:15,792
SHE ATTACKED THE LIONS,
SAVED THE ONE CUB,

203
00:14:15,792 --> 00:14:17,836
BUT THE OTHER WAS KILLED.

204
00:14:17,836 --> 00:14:19,213
IT WAS INCREDIBLE.

205
00:14:19,213 --> 00:14:21,381
SHE ATE PARTS OF THE DEAD CUB

206
00:14:21,381 --> 00:14:26,053
AND THEN BURIED THE REST
IN THE BRUSH.

207
00:14:27,512 --> 00:14:30,308
EVEN THOUGH WE’D BEEN PART
OF EVERY ASPECT OF HER LIFE,

208
00:14:30,308 --> 00:14:35,271
IT WAS SEVEN YEARS BEFORE
WE’RE ABLE TO FILM HER MATING.

209
00:14:35,271 --> 00:14:40,609
WE’VE REALLY SHARED HER LIFE
IN MANY WAYS.

210
00:14:40,609 --> 00:14:42,069
WE’VE SLEPT OUT
AT KILLS WITH HER.

211
00:14:42,069 --> 00:14:45,990
WE’VE WATCHED HER CUBS GROW UP
AND HAVE CUBS OF THEIR OWN.

212
00:14:45,990 --> 00:14:51,329
AND FOR ALL OF US, IT’S BEEN
A GREAT SPIRITUAL EXPERIENCE,

213
00:14:51,329 --> 00:14:52,746
ALMOST LIKE A LOVE AFFAIR,

214
00:14:52,746 --> 00:14:55,333
JUST TO BE PART OF HER LIFE.

215
00:14:55,333 --> 00:14:58,793
- SHE WAS THE MOST BEAUTIFUL
ANIMAL I HAD EVER SEEN.

216
00:14:58,793 --> 00:15:01,463
I UNDERSTOOD WHY JOHN AND ELMON
WERE SO DEDICATED TO HER.

217
00:15:01,463 --> 00:15:04,050
THE MORE I LEARNED
ABOUT HER LIFE,

218
00:15:04,050 --> 00:15:05,051
THE CLEARER IT BECAME TO ME

219
00:15:05,051 --> 00:15:08,095
THAT IT WAS HER STORY
THAT HAD TO BE TOLD.

220
00:15:08,095 --> 00:15:08,930
NOW IT WAS JUST A MATTER

221
00:15:08,930 --> 00:15:12,474
OF GETTING THE GREEN LIGHT
FROM DAN.

222
00:15:18,521 --> 00:15:19,899
- HI, CHRISTINE.
- HI, PAM.

223
00:15:19,899 --> 00:15:20,857
- HOW WAS YOUR TRIP?

224
00:15:20,857 --> 00:15:22,776
- IT WAS GREAT.
DID ANYTHING COME IN FOR ME?

225
00:15:22,776 --> 00:15:25,779
- THIS JUST CAME.
- OH, GREAT.

226
00:15:25,779 --> 00:15:26,864
HI.

227
00:15:26,864 --> 00:15:27,656
THANK YOU.

228
00:15:27,656 --> 00:15:29,200
HELLO,
- HI.

229
00:15:29,200 --> 00:15:31,534
- OH.
- I’M SO GLAD YOU’RE BACK.

230
00:15:31,534 --> 00:15:32,954
JACK IS DRIVING ME CRAZY.

231
00:15:32,954 --> 00:15:33,955
- THIS’LL SHUT HIM UP.

232
00:15:33,955 --> 00:15:35,122
- LET’S GO TO WORK.
- OKAY.

233
00:15:35,122 --> 00:15:36,332
AND I WANT TO HEAR
ALL ABOUT THIS.

234
00:15:36,332 --> 00:15:38,541
- BLACK RHINO POPULATIONS
OF AFRICA

235
00:15:38,541 --> 00:15:40,627
CONTINUALLY ON THE ROAD
TO OBLIVION.

236
00:15:40,627 --> 00:15:41,253
[gunshot]

237
00:15:41,253 --> 00:15:46,050
A SPECIES WHICH HAS BEEN AROUND
FOR 65 MILLION YEARS

238
00:15:46,050 --> 00:15:46,884
HAS, IN THE LAST DECADE,

239
00:15:46,884 --> 00:15:48,468
BEEN BROUGHT TO THE BRINK
OF EXTINCTION.

240
00:15:48,468 --> 00:15:52,223
MAN’S GREED AND POPULATIONS
CONTINUE UNHARNESSED.

241
00:15:52,223 --> 00:15:55,809
- THIS IS SOME OF THE FOOTAGE
THAT HE’S SHOT OVER THE YEARS.

242
00:15:55,809 --> 00:15:58,896
- I THOUGHT YOU WERE GONNA
COME UP WITH SOMETHING LIGHT,

243
00:15:58,896 --> 00:16:00,647
SOMETHING ENTERTAINING.

244
00:16:00,647 --> 00:16:03,109
WE PUT THIS ON, IT’S DEATH.

245
00:16:03,109 --> 00:16:04,110
IT’S DEPRESSING.

246
00:16:04,110 --> 00:16:05,027
NOBODY WANTS TO SEE IT.

247
00:16:05,027 --> 00:16:07,737
BESIDES, THEY CAN SEE IT
ON THE 6:00 NEWS.

248
00:16:07,737 --> 00:16:12,118
WHAT WE NEED
IS SOMETHING SPECIAL.

249
00:16:12,118 --> 00:16:14,870
- EXACTLY, JACK.

250
00:16:14,870 --> 00:16:18,748
AND THIS IS SPECIAL.

251
00:16:18,748 --> 00:16:22,461
VARTY LIVES IN A TREE
OUT IN THE MIDDLE OF THE BUSH.

252
00:16:22,461 --> 00:16:26,756
HE SPENDS HIS ENTIRE LIFE
FILMING WILDLIFE.

253
00:16:26,756 --> 00:16:28,926
HE’S DEDICATED THE LAST 12 YEARS

254
00:16:28,926 --> 00:16:30,970
TO FOLLOWING
A SINGLE FEMALE LEOPARD

255
00:16:30,970 --> 00:16:34,098
THROUGH EIGHT LITTERS OF CUBS.

256
00:16:34,098 --> 00:16:35,057
HE’S CAPTURED ON FILM

257
00:16:35,057 --> 00:16:39,979
SOME OF THE MOST SPECTACULAR
LEOPARD FOOTAGE EVER SHOT.

258
00:16:41,063 --> 00:16:44,442
TO TOP IT ALL OFF,
SHE NOW HAS TWO NEW CUBS

259
00:16:44,442 --> 00:16:48,570
THAT I’VE HAD
THE PRIVILEGE OF MEETING.

260
00:16:48,570 --> 00:16:51,449
THERE’S A GREAT STORY HERE.

261
00:16:55,702 --> 00:16:58,164
- NOT BAD, CHRIS.

262
00:16:58,164 --> 00:16:59,331
NOT BAD AT ALL.

263
00:16:59,331 --> 00:17:03,210
I WANT TO SEE A BUDGET
AND A FULL PROPOSAL.

264
00:17:06,422 --> 00:17:09,341
THANK YOU.

265
00:17:35,342 --> 00:17:37,843
- [roars]

266
00:17:39,845 --> 00:17:43,683
- [speaks African language]

267
00:17:46,311 --> 00:17:48,896
- GET OUT OF THERE, GIRL.

268
00:18:05,455 --> 00:18:09,167
[snarling and roaring]

269
00:18:22,430 --> 00:18:23,764
GET OUT!

270
00:18:23,764 --> 00:18:26,226
GET OUT OF THERE!

271
00:18:29,729 --> 00:18:33,525
[whispering and muttering]

272
00:18:47,330 --> 00:18:49,040
WATCH OUT!
WATCH OUT!

273
00:18:49,040 --> 00:18:49,873
FOLLOW, ELMON.

274
00:18:49,873 --> 00:18:52,669
[speaks African language]

275
00:19:03,430 --> 00:19:06,141
WATCH THESE TREES.

276
00:19:16,067 --> 00:19:17,818
KEEP GOING.
KEEP GOING.

277
00:19:17,818 --> 00:19:20,363
SHE WENT LEFT, ELMON.

278
00:19:20,363 --> 00:19:22,823
WATCH OUT.

279
00:19:25,660 --> 00:19:29,789
WAIT.
WHOA, WHOA, WHOA.

280
00:19:29,789 --> 00:19:31,207
SHH.
LISTEN.

281
00:19:31,207 --> 00:19:33,876
[snarling and roaring]

282
00:19:33,876 --> 00:19:36,004
I THINK THEY GOT HER, ELMON.

283
00:19:36,004 --> 00:19:39,090
[snarling]

284
00:19:42,594 --> 00:19:45,722
MUST TRY FIRST THING
IN THE MORNING TO FIND HER.

285
00:19:45,722 --> 00:19:47,057
- OKAY.

286
00:20:08,536 --> 00:20:11,997
[purring]

287
00:20:20,131 --> 00:20:22,509
- [speaking African language]

288
00:20:22,509 --> 00:20:24,010
- YEAH.

289
00:20:24,344 --> 00:20:28,431
[both speaking
African language]

290
00:20:44,155 --> 00:20:46,449
- OKAY.

291
00:20:47,742 --> 00:20:49,869
- OKAY.
- OKAY.

292
00:20:53,206 --> 00:20:56,251
[speaking African language]

293
00:21:03,174 --> 00:21:06,094
[speaking African language]

294
00:21:44,674 --> 00:21:48,303
[birds twittering]

295
00:21:55,768 --> 00:21:59,230
[mewling]

296
00:22:38,849 --> 00:22:42,187
- FOR ME, SHE HAD ALWAYS BEEN
THE ULTIMATE SURVIVOR.

297
00:22:42,187 --> 00:22:46,732
FOR 12 YEARS, SHE HAD BEEN
MY STRENGTH, MY INSPIRATION.

298
00:22:46,732 --> 00:22:50,986
PERHAPS I’D EVEN BELIEVED
SHE WAS INVINCIBLE.

299
00:22:50,986 --> 00:22:53,697
THE LIONS HAD CORNERED HER
MANY TIMES IN THE PAST,

300
00:22:53,697 --> 00:22:57,910
BUT THE YEARS
HAD SUDDENLY TAKEN THEIR TOLL.

301
00:22:57,910 --> 00:22:59,620
SHE WAS NO LONGER AS AGILE,

302
00:22:59,620 --> 00:23:02,457
AND NATURE ALLOWS
FOR NO WEAKNESS.

303
00:23:02,457 --> 00:23:06,627
FOR SO MANY YEARS, WE HAD SHARED
HER TRIUMPHS, HER SORROWS.

304
00:23:06,627 --> 00:23:09,089
SHE WAS MY SOUL MATE,

305
00:23:09,089 --> 00:23:11,091
AND NOW SHE WAS DYING.

306
00:23:40,703 --> 00:23:42,955
- THE BUDGET.

307
00:23:42,955 --> 00:23:43,664
- UH-OH.

308
00:23:43,664 --> 00:23:45,208
- I KNOW.
I’M TRYING TO BRING IT DOWN.

309
00:23:45,208 --> 00:23:48,752
- DAN, I HAD VALERIE
DO SOME GROUNDWORK

310
00:23:48,752 --> 00:23:49,712
ON THIS VARTY CHARACTER.

311
00:23:49,712 --> 00:23:50,880
HE’S A BIT OF A LOOSE CANNON.

312
00:23:50,880 --> 00:23:52,382
NEVER REALLY BROUGHT ANYTHING
IN ON TIME.

313
00:23:52,382 --> 00:23:55,552
PROBABLY DOESN’T KNOW THE
MEANING OF THE WORD "BUDGET."

314
00:23:55,552 --> 00:23:56,469
- OH, COME ON, JACK.

315
00:23:56,469 --> 00:23:58,513
- CHRIS, DON’T GET ME WRONG.
I’M ON YOUR SIDE.

316
00:23:58,513 --> 00:24:01,474
IT’S JUST I DON’T WANT TO HAVE
TO COME IN AND CLEAN UP WHEN--

317
00:24:01,474 --> 00:24:03,767
EXCUSE ME--
IF THINGS GET OUT OF CONTROL.

318
00:24:03,767 --> 00:24:06,396
- WHAT ARE YOU GETTING AT, JACK?

319
00:24:06,396 --> 00:24:08,731
- CAN YOU DELIVER THIS TIME?

320
00:24:08,731 --> 00:24:10,066
- OKAY, JACK.
WE GET THE POINT.

321
00:24:10,066 --> 00:24:12,860
AND EVERYONE KNOWS THAT WHAT
HAPPENED WITH THE LAST PROJECT

322
00:24:12,860 --> 00:24:14,237
WAS NOT ENTIRELY
CHRISTINE’S FAULT.

323
00:24:14,237 --> 00:24:16,406
BUT THIS IS THE KIND
OF PROJECT WE REALLY NEED.

324
00:24:16,406 --> 00:24:17,823
IT’S DIFFERENT.
- DIFFERENT.

325
00:24:17,823 --> 00:24:18,782
- IT’S HIGH-PROFILE.

326
00:24:18,782 --> 00:24:20,993
IT’S THE KIND OF THING
THAT CAN PULL US BACK UP.

327
00:24:20,993 --> 00:24:21,661
- YES, SIR.

328
00:24:21,661 --> 00:24:23,121
- BUT IT’S UP TO YOU, CHRISTINE.

329
00:24:23,121 --> 00:24:25,915
I’M NOT GONNA BABYSIT YOU
ON THIS PROJECT.

330
00:24:31,087 --> 00:24:33,506
YOU’VE BEEN OUT THERE.
YOU KNOW THE TERRITORY.

331
00:24:33,506 --> 00:24:35,008
YOU KNOW THIS GUY VARTY.

332
00:24:35,008 --> 00:24:36,343
YOU KNOW WHAT I NEED.

333
00:24:36,343 --> 00:24:38,345
THIS PROJECT MEANS A LOT TO ME.

334
00:24:38,345 --> 00:24:39,887
I’M COUNTING ON YOU, KID.

335
00:24:39,887 --> 00:24:43,183
- UH, YES, MR. VARTY--WALKER.

336
00:24:43,183 --> 00:24:45,976
- ALL RIGHT.

337
00:25:10,876 --> 00:25:14,714
[both speaking African language]

338
00:25:16,466 --> 00:25:19,135
- WE’VE GOT TO FIND THOSE CUBS,
ELMON.

339
00:25:19,135 --> 00:25:21,263
- [speaks African language]

340
00:25:22,222 --> 00:25:25,766
[cubs purring]

341
00:26:53,730 --> 00:26:57,233
[animal hooting]

342
00:27:18,046 --> 00:27:21,549
[lion snorting]

343
00:27:46,783 --> 00:27:50,412
[birds twittering]

344
00:27:58,086 --> 00:27:59,421
- AH, THEY’RE NOT HERE.

345
00:27:59,421 --> 00:28:01,464
- [speaks African language]

346
00:28:01,922 --> 00:28:04,426
- [speaks African language]

347
00:28:11,516 --> 00:28:14,185
- WHOA, WHOA, WHOA.

348
00:28:18,106 --> 00:28:21,942
[speaking African language]

349
00:28:33,705 --> 00:28:35,373
- [speaking African language]

350
00:28:35,373 --> 00:28:38,877
- [chanting]

351
00:28:44,757 --> 00:28:48,969
- ELMON WENT TO ASK THE SPIRITS
WHERE WE MIGHT FIND THE CUBS

352
00:28:48,969 --> 00:28:50,346
WHILE I PORED OVER MY MAPS

353
00:28:50,346 --> 00:28:53,266
WHICH PLOTTED
HER TERRITORIAL BOUNDARIES

354
00:28:53,266 --> 00:28:55,059
AND FAVORITE DEN SITES.

355
00:28:55,059 --> 00:28:59,189
[both chanting
in African language]

356
00:29:07,822 --> 00:29:09,491
ELMON.
- YEAH?

357
00:29:09,491 --> 00:29:12,744
- COME LOOK HERE.

358
00:29:12,744 --> 00:29:14,704
I THINK I’VE GOT IT.

359
00:29:14,704 --> 00:29:18,541
[speaking African language]

360
00:29:31,513 --> 00:29:33,348
ELMON.
- YEAH?

361
00:29:33,348 --> 00:29:35,141
- [speaking African language]

362
00:29:35,141 --> 00:29:37,477
- OKAY.

363
00:29:48,196 --> 00:29:52,283
[both speaking
African language]

364
00:30:08,299 --> 00:30:09,634
HEH.

365
00:30:09,634 --> 00:30:12,095
[speaking African language]

366
00:30:12,428 --> 00:30:16,516
[both speaking
African language]

367
00:30:26,943 --> 00:30:28,278
- OKAY.

368
00:30:28,278 --> 00:30:32,156
- [speaking African language]

369
00:31:37,805 --> 00:31:38,431
- J.V.!

370
00:31:38,431 --> 00:31:39,682
- HEY, JIMMY.
HOW YOU DOING?

371
00:31:39,682 --> 00:31:40,892
- GOOD.
- LONG TIME, NO SEE.

372
00:31:40,892 --> 00:31:42,810
YEAH, GOOD.
GOOD, GOOD.

373
00:31:42,810 --> 00:31:43,728
- WHAT’S THAT FOR?

374
00:31:43,728 --> 00:31:44,771
- OH, I GOT SOME BABY LEOPARDS.

375
00:31:44,771 --> 00:31:46,106
- OH?
- YEAH, LIONS KILLED THE MOTHER.

376
00:31:46,106 --> 00:31:48,316
- OH, POOR THINGS.
- YEAH, A COUPLE OF WEEKS OLD.

377
00:31:48,316 --> 00:31:49,525
THEY’RE DOING WELL.
- HUH.

378
00:31:49,525 --> 00:31:51,028
- YEAH, THIS IS GOOD STUFF,
THEY TELL ME.

379
00:31:51,028 --> 00:31:52,445
AND YOU?
PROBLEMS WITH THE POACHING?

380
00:31:52,445 --> 00:31:54,322
- OH, YOU KNOW ME.
I’M STILL AS FAST.

381
00:31:54,322 --> 00:31:55,239
- AH, THAT’S GOOD.

382
00:31:55,239 --> 00:31:56,699
AND THE CAMP?
WHERE’S THE CAMP NOW?

383
00:31:56,699 --> 00:31:58,201
- OH, FIVE MILES SOUTH
FROM HERE.

384
00:31:58,201 --> 00:31:59,535
- UH-HUH.
ON THE RIVER, EH?

385
00:31:59,535 --> 00:32:00,995
- YEAH, YOU KNOW ME.
- OKAY.

386
00:32:00,995 --> 00:32:04,124
OKAY.
[speaks African language]

387
00:32:06,626 --> 00:32:09,712
HELLO, IS THAT
"GLOBAL EXPLORER?"

388
00:32:09,712 --> 00:32:12,340
[speaks African language]

389
00:32:12,340 --> 00:32:12,882
YEAH.

390
00:32:12,882 --> 00:32:14,175
IS CHRISTINE SHAYE THERE
BY ANY CHANCE?

391
00:32:14,175 --> 00:32:16,719
- SHE’S NOT IN RIGHT NOW.
CAN I TAKE A MESSAGE?

392
00:32:16,719 --> 00:32:20,264
- YEAH, TELL HER
I HAVE FOUND THE CUBS.

393
00:32:20,264 --> 00:32:21,766
THAT’S LEOPARD CUBS.

394
00:32:21,766 --> 00:32:23,976
- CAN I GIVE HER A NUMBER
SO SHE CAN CALL YOU BACK?

395
00:32:23,976 --> 00:32:26,146
- NO, UNFORTUNATELY,
I’M AT LONDOLOZI

396
00:32:26,146 --> 00:32:28,189
IN A REMOTE PART
OF SOUTH AFRICA.

397
00:32:28,189 --> 00:32:30,191
JUST TELL HER J.V. PHONED.

398
00:32:30,191 --> 00:32:32,568
AND SEE THAT SHE GETS
THAT MESSAGE.

399
00:32:32,568 --> 00:32:33,861
- OH, MR. VARTY.

400
00:32:33,861 --> 00:32:35,155
OH, YEAH, SURE.

401
00:32:35,155 --> 00:32:36,489
I’LL TELL HER YOU CALLED.

402
00:32:36,489 --> 00:32:41,703
HAVE A NICE DAY.
BYE.

403
00:32:42,954 --> 00:32:45,248
- WELL, I’M NOT QUITE SURE
HOW TO PUT IT.

404
00:32:45,248 --> 00:32:49,128
- WHY DON’T YOU JUST SAY IT,
CHRIS?

405
00:32:49,128 --> 00:32:55,967
- UM, I JUST GOT WORD
THAT THE MOTHER LEOPARD IS DEAD.

406
00:32:57,136 --> 00:33:00,638
- THAT’S FOR CHRISTINE.

407
00:33:00,638 --> 00:33:03,266
- I’M HEADED THAT WAY.

408
00:33:03,599 --> 00:33:05,018
[phone rings]

409
00:33:05,018 --> 00:33:07,270
- I’M NOT EVEN SURE
WHAT HAPPENED,

410
00:33:07,270 --> 00:33:11,566
BUT I WAS THINKING THAT
WE STILL HAVE A STRONG STORY

411
00:33:11,566 --> 00:33:13,026
IF WE CAN FIND HER CUBS.

412
00:33:13,026 --> 00:33:14,610
I’VE BEEN TRYING
TO GET AHOLD OF J.V.

413
00:33:14,610 --> 00:33:15,820
TO SEE IF THEY’RE STILL ALIVE.

414
00:33:15,820 --> 00:33:19,615
- YOU KNOW, I REALLY STUCK
MY NECK OUT ON THIS PROJECT.

415
00:33:19,615 --> 00:33:21,076
- I KNOW YOU HAVE, SIR.

416
00:33:21,076 --> 00:33:22,493
[knocking]

417
00:33:22,493 --> 00:33:24,412
- MY SCREENING’S AT 3:30.

418
00:33:24,412 --> 00:33:25,747
HOPE I’M NOT INTERRUPTING.

419
00:33:25,747 --> 00:33:28,125
- NO.
COME IN, JACK.

420
00:33:28,125 --> 00:33:29,667
THE LEOPARD’S DEAD.

421
00:33:29,667 --> 00:33:30,710
- OH, NO.

422
00:33:30,710 --> 00:33:33,254
- AND I DON’T KNOW
IF THIS COMPANY CAN SURVIVE

423
00:33:33,254 --> 00:33:34,131
ANOTHER FAILED PROJECT.

424
00:33:34,131 --> 00:33:37,341
- I REALIZE THAT, UM, BUT,
WHAT THE MOTHER LEOPARD DOES IS,

425
00:33:37,341 --> 00:33:38,551
SHE MOVES HER CUBS
FROM DEN TO DEN.

426
00:33:38,551 --> 00:33:41,679
I’M SURE IT’S A MATTER OF TIME
BEFORE J.V. FINDS THEM.

427
00:33:41,679 --> 00:33:42,930
- ALL DUE RESPECT, CHRISTINE,

428
00:33:42,930 --> 00:33:47,144
YOU’VE BEEN SURE
OF A LOT OF THINGS IN THE PAST.

429
00:33:47,144 --> 00:33:51,314
- LOOK, JACK, WE ALREADY HAVE
12 YEARS OF LEOPARD FOOTAGE

430
00:33:51,314 --> 00:33:52,565
THAT WE CAN WORK WITH.

431
00:33:52,565 --> 00:33:55,485
- STOCK FOOTAGE
FOR AN ENTIRE PROGRAM?

432
00:33:55,485 --> 00:33:56,402
YOU MUST BE KIDDING.

433
00:33:56,402 --> 00:34:02,242
CHRISTINE, ALL YOU HAVE
TO OFFER IS ONE DEAD LEOPARD.

434
00:34:02,242 --> 00:34:03,326
ALL WE HAVE IS ONE DEAD PROJECT.

435
00:34:03,326 --> 00:34:05,745
- PLEASE, MR. WALKER,
JUST GIVE ME A FEW WEEKS,

436
00:34:05,745 --> 00:34:09,582
AND I CAN WORK SOMETHING OUT.

437
00:34:09,582 --> 00:34:11,959
- YOU’VE GOT ONE WEEK, CHRIS.

438
00:34:11,959 --> 00:34:14,462
- THANK YOU.

439
00:34:16,131 --> 00:34:17,507
- LOOK WHAT I’VE GOT FOR YOU.

440
00:34:17,507 --> 00:34:18,883
- [speaks African language]

441
00:34:18,883 --> 00:34:20,843
- COME ON, PRETTY BOY.

442
00:34:20,843 --> 00:34:22,929
AH, SISTER.

443
00:34:22,929 --> 00:34:26,766
[speaking African language]

444
00:34:30,603 --> 00:34:33,564
LITTLE TOUGHY, EH?

445
00:34:33,564 --> 00:34:34,857
LITTLE TOUGHY.

446
00:34:34,857 --> 00:34:35,566
YEAH.

447
00:34:35,566 --> 00:34:39,737
DRINK IT.
DON’T BITE THE BOTTLE.

448
00:34:40,988 --> 00:34:42,865
THAT’S MY BOY.

449
00:34:42,865 --> 00:34:44,367
THAT’S MY GIRLY GIRL.

450
00:34:44,367 --> 00:34:48,329
- [speaks African language]

451
00:34:48,329 --> 00:34:51,332
- I SHOULD’VE USED THIS.

452
00:34:56,587 --> 00:35:00,050
- [speaking African language]

453
00:35:32,665 --> 00:35:35,168
- [chuckles]

454
00:36:12,872 --> 00:36:14,041
- COME ON, YOU GUYS.

455
00:36:14,041 --> 00:36:15,334
- OKAY, LET’S GO FOR WALK.

456
00:36:15,334 --> 00:36:17,960
- COME ON.
HAVE A WALK NOW.

457
00:36:17,960 --> 00:36:20,421
[whistles]

458
00:36:22,632 --> 00:36:23,591
COME ON, SISTER.

459
00:36:23,591 --> 00:36:25,593
LET’S WALK.

460
00:36:28,930 --> 00:36:29,680
- HELLO.

461
00:36:29,680 --> 00:36:31,933
IS THIS THE HAZYVIEW HOTEL?

462
00:36:31,933 --> 00:36:33,434
CAN YOU HELP ME, PLEASE?

463
00:36:33,434 --> 00:36:36,729
YEAH, I HAVE TO GET AHOLD
OF J.V., OKAY?

464
00:36:36,729 --> 00:36:38,148
JOHN VARTY.

465
00:36:38,148 --> 00:36:40,359
DOES ANYONE KNOW WHERE HE IS?

466
00:36:40,359 --> 00:36:43,903
HAS HE LEFT ANY MESSAGES?

467
00:36:43,903 --> 00:36:44,612
OH, OKAY.

468
00:36:44,612 --> 00:36:45,655
LOOK, IF YOU DO SPEAK TO HIM,

469
00:36:45,655 --> 00:36:49,909
TELL HIM IT’S VERY IMPORTANT
THAT I TALK TO HIM.

470
00:36:49,909 --> 00:36:51,452
NUH-HUH.

471
00:36:51,452 --> 00:36:53,913
OKAY, BYE.

472
00:36:53,913 --> 00:36:56,707
[sighs]

473
00:37:01,504 --> 00:37:04,132
- "SO I AM LEFT
IN THE DIFFICULT POSITION

474
00:37:04,132 --> 00:37:09,887
"OF HAVING TO HAND-RAISE
HER TWO ORPHAN CUBS

475
00:37:09,887 --> 00:37:13,308
"WITH THE INTENTION
OF REINTRODUCING THEM

476
00:37:13,308 --> 00:37:15,851
INTO THE WILDS."

477
00:37:15,851 --> 00:37:18,562
[leopard mewling and chirping]

478
00:37:18,562 --> 00:37:20,399
HEY, COME ON.

479
00:37:23,193 --> 00:37:24,527
YOU’RE FUNNY, MAN.

480
00:37:24,527 --> 00:37:27,197
"I BELIEVE YOUR OFFICE
IS RESPONSIBLE

481
00:37:27,197 --> 00:37:28,489
"FOR ISSUING SUCH PERMITS,

482
00:37:28,489 --> 00:37:35,788
AND I WOULD APPRECIATE YOUR
