484
00:38:18,165 --> 00:38:20,750
- MR. VARTY.

485
00:38:20,750 --> 00:38:22,710
- UP HERE.

486
00:38:28,799 --> 00:38:29,384
- VARTY.

487
00:38:29,384 --> 00:38:31,344
- MR. VAN HEERDEN.
- YEAH.

488
00:38:31,344 --> 00:38:32,553
- HI.

489
00:38:32,553 --> 00:38:34,139
- WE RECEIVED YOUR LETTER.

490
00:38:34,139 --> 00:38:37,808
UNFORTUNATELY, WE’RE UNABLE
TO PROCESS YOUR REQUEST.

491
00:38:37,808 --> 00:38:41,104
UNLESS YOU MAKE
A FORMAL APPLICATION.

492
00:38:41,104 --> 00:38:42,980
- UGH.

493
00:38:42,980 --> 00:38:44,232
WHAT’S THE PROBLEM?

494
00:38:44,232 --> 00:38:47,069
TAKE A SEAT.

495
00:38:47,069 --> 00:38:49,570
- THERE HAVE BEEN
SOME COMPLAINTS.

496
00:38:49,570 --> 00:38:51,031
- LIKE, FROM WHO?

497
00:38:51,031 --> 00:38:51,697
- [chuckles]

498
00:38:51,697 --> 00:38:57,162
IT’S NOT OUR POLICY
TO DIVULGE THAT INFORMATION.

499
00:38:57,162 --> 00:39:01,166
THIS ANIMAL SHOULD REALLY
BE KEPT IN A CAGE.

500
00:39:01,166 --> 00:39:05,420
WHAT IF ONE WANDER OFF AND
TAKES SOMEONE’S DOMESTIC CATTLE?

501
00:39:05,420 --> 00:39:06,505
- AH, COME ON.
COME ON.

502
00:39:06,505 --> 00:39:09,007
YOU KNOW THERE’S A PROCLAIMED
GAME RESERVE HERE.

503
00:39:09,007 --> 00:39:10,883
THERE’S NO STOCK FOR MILES.

504
00:39:10,883 --> 00:39:13,594
- OFF THE RECORD,
I AGREE WITH YOU.

505
00:39:13,594 --> 00:39:16,014
BUT THE LAW IS QUITE CLEAR
ON THE ISSUE

506
00:39:16,014 --> 00:39:17,432
OF HAND-RAISING OF WILD ANIMALS.

507
00:39:17,432 --> 00:39:20,143
THEY MUST BE KEPT
SECURELY CONTAINED

508
00:39:20,143 --> 00:39:21,394
IN A CAGE OR ENCLOSURE,

509
00:39:21,394 --> 00:39:25,065
FAILING WHICH,
THEY WILL BE DESTROYED.

510
00:39:25,065 --> 00:39:26,649
- SO UNDER YOUR RULES,

511
00:39:26,649 --> 00:39:29,569
THEY’RE GONNA END UP
IN A FILTHY ZOO,

512
00:39:29,569 --> 00:39:30,403
PACING UP AND DOWN.

513
00:39:30,403 --> 00:39:35,200
WITH ME, THEY’VE GOT A CHANCE
AT RUNNING FREE.

514
00:39:35,200 --> 00:39:38,078
- WE ARE ON THE SAME SIDE,
MR. VARTY,

515
00:39:38,078 --> 00:39:39,454
BUT MY HANDS ARE TIED.

516
00:39:39,454 --> 00:39:41,123
PERHAPS I CAN--

517
00:39:41,123 --> 00:39:44,584
[snarling]

518
00:39:46,752 --> 00:39:47,711
- GIVE IT HERE.

519
00:39:47,711 --> 00:39:50,006
GIVE ME THAT.

520
00:39:50,006 --> 00:39:52,300
COME ON, GIVE ME THE HAT.

521
00:39:52,300 --> 00:39:54,885
DON’T EAT MR. VAN HEERDEN’S HAT.

522
00:39:54,885 --> 00:39:56,263
HOLD ON.

523
00:39:56,263 --> 00:39:57,472
HEY.

524
00:39:57,472 --> 00:39:58,722
GIVE ME THAT.

525
00:39:58,722 --> 00:39:59,932
LITTLE BOY, GIVE ME THE HAT.

526
00:39:59,932 --> 00:40:00,850
- WHAT ABOUT RABIES?

527
00:40:00,850 --> 00:40:04,770
I’M AFRAID THIS WILL HAVE TO GO
IN MY REPORT, MR. VARTY.

528
00:40:13,654 --> 00:40:15,031
- YOUR HAT.

529
00:40:15,031 --> 00:40:21,037
- MR. VARTY, I WOULD RECOMMEND
YOU MAKE A PLAN IN A HURRY.

530
00:40:23,248 --> 00:40:25,375
IT’S FOR THE BEST, YOU KNOW.

531
00:40:25,375 --> 00:40:29,087
HERE IS YOUR APPLICATIONS.

532
00:40:29,087 --> 00:40:33,592
THESE ANIMALS SHOULD NOT BE
RUNNING WILD.

533
00:40:36,219 --> 00:40:40,223
- GREAT P.R. JOB YOU DID.

534
00:40:45,353 --> 00:40:47,980
[speaking African language]

535
00:40:47,980 --> 00:40:50,275
THAT’S A TORTOISE, SISTER.

536
00:40:50,275 --> 00:40:53,320
THAT’S A TORTOISE.

537
00:40:53,320 --> 00:40:55,655
COME ON.

538
00:41:00,118 --> 00:41:02,329
HEY, SISTER.

539
00:41:02,329 --> 00:41:04,623
SISTER.

540
00:41:08,084 --> 00:41:09,127
UGH.
RAN OUT.

541
00:41:09,127 --> 00:41:11,046
- J.V.
- YUP.

542
00:41:11,046 --> 00:41:14,049
- [speaks African language]
- OH, COME ON.

543
00:41:14,049 --> 00:41:15,258
GET ANOTHER ROLL.

544
00:41:15,258 --> 00:41:16,676
- NO MORE FILM STOCK.

545
00:41:16,676 --> 00:41:18,470
- UGH.
COME ON.

546
00:41:18,470 --> 00:41:22,224
LOOK AT THE SHOT WE’RE MISSING.

547
00:41:22,224 --> 00:41:23,058
GOT THE CAP?

548
00:41:23,058 --> 00:41:26,727
- NOT IN THE CAMERA.

549
00:41:28,729 --> 00:41:30,898
- HOW CAN WE WORK LIKE THIS?

550
00:41:30,898 --> 00:41:35,237
- WHY NOT PHONE THE STORE?

551
00:41:36,029 --> 00:41:38,323
- BEAUTIFUL SHOT.

552
00:41:38,323 --> 00:41:41,284
[speaks African language]

553
00:41:41,284 --> 00:41:43,827
- HI, CHRISTINE.
J.V. HERE.

554
00:41:43,827 --> 00:41:44,954
I’M GETTING REALLY WORRIED

555
00:41:44,954 --> 00:41:47,831
BECAUSE THESE CUBS
ARE GETTING BIG NOW,

556
00:41:47,831 --> 00:41:54,089
AND I CAN JUST FEEL THIS PROJECT
STARTING TO SLIP AWAY.

557
00:41:54,089 --> 00:41:55,507
I GOT A FANTASTIC SEQUENCE.

558
00:41:55,507 --> 00:42:01,929
I’VE BEEN TAKING SOME FISH
OUT OF THE--AAGH!

559
00:42:01,929 --> 00:42:03,098
YOU MONSTER!

560
00:42:03,098 --> 00:42:05,558
AH, THAT WAS A CUB.
JUST BIT ME ON THE TOE.

561
00:42:05,558 --> 00:42:06,101
OKAY.

562
00:42:06,101 --> 00:42:08,645
ANYWAY, THEY CAUGHT THESE FISH
IN A DRYING POOL,

563
00:42:08,645 --> 00:42:12,357
AND THEN I LOST--
THE CAMERA BROKE,

564
00:42:12,357 --> 00:42:14,276
AND I HAD TO SEND THAT IN
FOR TWO WEEKS,

565
00:42:14,276 --> 00:42:16,319
BUT PLEASE, LET ME KNOW
ONE WAY OR THE OTHER

566
00:42:16,319 --> 00:42:18,904
BECAUSE THIS IS
A FANTASTIC PROJECT,

567
00:42:18,904 --> 00:42:21,907
AND WE’VE GOT TO GET GOING NOW.

568
00:42:23,326 --> 00:42:25,786
- AND HOW ABOUT
A SWEET DEPOSIT?

569
00:42:25,786 --> 00:42:27,289
HOW DOES THAT SOUND TO YOU, HUH?

570
00:42:27,289 --> 00:42:29,165
OH, YEAH. VERIFY--

571
00:42:29,165 --> 00:42:31,376
- JACK.
WILL YOU EXCUSE US, VALERIE?

572
00:42:31,376 --> 00:42:34,713
PAM SAID SHE GAVE YOU
THE MESSAGE.

573
00:42:34,713 --> 00:42:35,505
- WHAT MESSAGE?

574
00:42:35,505 --> 00:42:38,924
- I JUST GOT THIS FAX.
THE CUBS ARE ALREADY ON MEAT.

575
00:42:38,924 --> 00:42:40,510
J.V. FOUND THEM WEEKS AGO.

576
00:42:40,510 --> 00:42:41,927
- YOU GO TELL DAN

577
00:42:41,927 --> 00:42:46,308
THAT WHAT WE HAVE IS NO LONGER
A DEAD PROJECT.

578
00:42:46,308 --> 00:42:49,477
SO LONG, JACK.

579
00:42:49,477 --> 00:42:52,980
[jet engine whining]

580
00:43:14,753 --> 00:43:15,836
[laughter]

581
00:43:15,836 --> 00:43:17,172
- I REMEMBER YOU.

582
00:43:17,172 --> 00:43:17,963
THANK YOU.

583
00:43:17,963 --> 00:43:18,839
- THANKS A LOT, LESTER.

584
00:43:18,839 --> 00:43:21,343
- OKAY, TAKE CARE,
MISS CHRISTINE.

585
00:43:21,343 --> 00:43:22,218
- WHERE’S J.V.?

586
00:43:22,218 --> 00:43:25,722
- J.V.’S WENT TO HESIVI
THIS MORNING.

587
00:43:25,722 --> 00:43:27,057
TRY SOME GET A PERMIT.

588
00:43:27,057 --> 00:43:28,558
- PERMIT FOR WHAT?

589
00:43:28,558 --> 00:43:29,892
- OH, FOR THE LEOPARDS.

590
00:43:29,892 --> 00:43:31,227
- [gasps]

591
00:43:31,227 --> 00:43:33,355
ARE THEY STILL BABIES?

592
00:43:33,355 --> 00:43:34,397
OH, GOD.

593
00:43:34,397 --> 00:43:35,815
CAN I GO UP TO ’EM?
- YEAH.

594
00:43:35,815 --> 00:43:38,234
CAREFUL.
THEY STILL GOT CLAWS, THOUGH.

595
00:43:38,234 --> 00:43:39,860
- OKAY.

596
00:43:41,488 --> 00:43:43,864
OH, GOD.
SHE’S SO PRETTY.

597
00:43:43,864 --> 00:43:45,158
LOOK AT HER LITTLE FACE.

598
00:43:45,158 --> 00:43:47,577
OH, ELMON,
IT’S SO GOOD TO BE BACK.

599
00:43:47,577 --> 00:43:49,079
- YEAH.

600
00:43:49,079 --> 00:43:50,497
- CAN I TOUCH HER?

601
00:43:50,497 --> 00:43:51,456
- OH, JUST BE CAREFUL

602
00:43:51,456 --> 00:43:53,666
OF THE CLAW DOES NOT HOOK YOU.

603
00:43:53,666 --> 00:43:56,877
- I’M HOOKED ALREADY.

604
00:43:56,877 --> 00:43:57,878
HEY, LITTLE GIRL.

605
00:43:57,878 --> 00:44:01,132
HEY, LITTLE GIRL.
OH.

606
00:44:23,029 --> 00:44:23,696
[laughs]

607
00:44:23,696 --> 00:44:28,410
WHAT ARE YOU GUYS
DOING UP THERE, HUH?

608
00:44:28,410 --> 00:44:30,286
WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO?

609
00:44:30,286 --> 00:44:31,830
OH, WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO?

610
00:44:31,830 --> 00:44:32,747
HUH?

611
00:44:32,747 --> 00:44:33,623
WHAT DO YOU WANT TO DO?

612
00:44:33,623 --> 00:44:35,083
YOU WANT TO TAKE A SHOWER?

613
00:44:35,083 --> 00:44:36,000
HUH?

614
00:44:36,000 --> 00:44:36,709
OH, I GET IT.

615
00:44:36,709 --> 00:44:41,798
YOU’RE GONNA DRINK MY WATER.

616
00:44:41,798 --> 00:44:42,507
- OH, GOOD.

617
00:44:42,507 --> 00:44:45,885
- J.V., I’M REALLY SORRY
ABOUT THE MOTHER.

618
00:44:45,885 --> 00:44:48,263
- YEAH, THAT’S LIFE.

619
00:44:48,263 --> 00:44:51,391
- BUT I CAN’T WAIT TO SEE
WHAT YOU’VE BEEN GETTING.

620
00:44:51,391 --> 00:44:53,309
HEY, LITTLE MAN.

621
00:44:56,062 --> 00:44:58,314
- JUST MIND: IT’S NEGATIVE.

622
00:44:58,314 --> 00:44:58,981
- NEGATIVE?

623
00:44:58,981 --> 00:45:00,859
WHAT ARE YOU DOING,
KEEPING THE NEGATIVE HERE?

624
00:45:00,859 --> 00:45:03,736
- EH, STORAGE AT THE LABS
ARE SO EXPENSIVE.

625
00:45:03,736 --> 00:45:08,366
- WELL, I CAN SEE WE’VE GOT SOME
SORTING OUT TO DO.

626
00:45:08,366 --> 00:45:10,118
HA--HEY, HEY, HEY!
COME HERE!

627
00:45:10,118 --> 00:45:11,952
COME HERE!
LEAVE THE FILM ALONE.

628
00:45:11,952 --> 00:45:13,413
- HEY, BRING BACK MY FILM.

629
00:45:13,413 --> 00:45:14,997
MONSTER.

630
00:45:17,834 --> 00:45:19,711
COME, LITTLE BOY.
COME, GIRLY.

631
00:45:19,711 --> 00:45:23,298
YOU WANT TO WATCH
OUR MOVIE STARS.

632
00:45:23,298 --> 00:45:23,964
AH, YOU SEE NOW.

633
00:45:23,964 --> 00:45:25,800
LOOK HOW--
THIS IS JUST PURE INSTINCT.

634
00:45:25,800 --> 00:45:28,595
HOW YOU HOIST THAT HARE
STRAIGHT UP THE TREE.

635
00:45:28,595 --> 00:45:32,182
HE’S NEVER SEEN
HIS MOTHER DO THAT.

636
00:45:32,182 --> 00:45:34,017
THIS IS A GREAT SHOT.

637
00:45:34,017 --> 00:45:38,605
THESE CATFISH WERE TRAPPED
IN THIS MUDDY POOL.

638
00:45:38,605 --> 00:45:40,690
LOOK AT THAT.

639
00:45:40,690 --> 00:45:41,608
BEAUTIFUL.

640
00:45:41,608 --> 00:45:42,525
- SO ADORABLE!

641
00:45:42,525 --> 00:45:45,278
- AH, YOU SEE, THIS IS ALL
TRAINING FOR LATER LIFE.

642
00:45:45,278 --> 00:45:46,279
- [chuckles]

643
00:45:46,279 --> 00:45:48,823
- THEY DON’T CALL THEM
THE PERFECT PREDATOR

644
00:45:48,823 --> 00:45:50,575
FOR NOTHING, YOU KNOW?

645
00:45:50,575 --> 00:45:51,910
THESE GUYS CAN SURVIVE
ON ANYTHING.

646
00:45:51,910 --> 00:45:55,413
LITTLE CUB, AND HE CATCHES
HIS FISH, NO PROBLEM.

647
00:45:55,413 --> 00:45:59,042
CLAWS, TEETH,
EVERYTHING WORKING.

648
00:45:59,042 --> 00:46:00,627
- [laughs]

649
00:46:00,627 --> 00:46:02,462
- HE’S GOT IT DOWN.

650
00:46:02,462 --> 00:46:05,632
- OH, THAT WAS SO...

651
00:46:54,055 --> 00:46:56,641
WHAT A WAKE-UP CALL.

652
00:47:00,020 --> 00:47:02,105
J.V.!

653
00:47:16,578 --> 00:47:17,370
- STEVENS.

654
00:47:17,370 --> 00:47:18,204
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

655
00:47:18,204 --> 00:47:20,081
- I’M HERE FOR THOSE RHINO HORNS
YOU PROMISED ME.

656
00:47:20,081 --> 00:47:23,376
- MAN, YOU SHOULD NOT BE SEEN
IN THIS OFFICE.

657
00:47:23,376 --> 00:47:24,085
- RELAX, MAN.

658
00:47:24,085 --> 00:47:26,421
I’M HERE
FOR AN IMPORT/EXPORT PERMIT.

659
00:47:26,421 --> 00:47:29,799
LISTEN, I’VE GOT
A DEFINITE BUYER FOR--

660
00:47:29,799 --> 00:47:31,175
- NOT HERE.
NOT HERE.

661
00:47:31,175 --> 00:47:34,762
- HEY, I HAVE GOT A BUYER
FOR THOSE TWO CUBS.

662
00:47:34,762 --> 00:47:36,598
- VARTY’S CUBS?

663
00:47:38,058 --> 00:47:39,684
- OH, THIS IS GOOD.

664
00:47:39,684 --> 00:47:41,311
GREAT.

665
00:47:47,067 --> 00:47:51,738
OKAY, MOVE IN
A LITTLE BIT CLOSER.

666
00:47:58,578 --> 00:48:00,663
- THAT’S-A-BOY.
- GREAT.

667
00:48:00,663 --> 00:48:01,414
- THAT’S-A-BOY.

668
00:48:01,414 --> 00:48:02,415
- OKAY, YOU GET A CLOSE-UP,

669
00:48:02,415 --> 00:48:06,919
AND I’LL GET THE TWO OF YOU
IN FRAME.

670
00:48:06,919 --> 00:48:08,129
WHAT A GREAT SHOT.

671
00:48:08,129 --> 00:48:09,547
OH, THIS IS PERFECT.

672
00:48:09,547 --> 00:48:12,759
GOT BOTH OF YOU.

673
00:48:12,759 --> 00:48:16,096
HE WANTS HIS OWN CLOSE-UP.

674
00:48:23,603 --> 00:48:25,105
- HI, CHRISTINE.
- HI, ELMON.

675
00:48:25,105 --> 00:48:26,189
I BRING MY SON, TIDI.

676
00:48:26,189 --> 00:48:28,358
- OH, GREAT.
HI, TIDI.

677
00:48:28,358 --> 00:48:29,651
- HI.

678
00:48:29,651 --> 00:48:33,529
- GO SAY HI.
GO SAY HI TO THEM.

679
00:48:48,795 --> 00:48:50,296
- HELLO, SISTER.

680
00:48:50,296 --> 00:48:53,174
WHERE’S YOUR BROTHER?

681
00:48:55,094 --> 00:48:56,386
COME, BROTHER.

682
00:48:56,386 --> 00:48:59,639
COME, COME, COME.

683
00:49:04,310 --> 00:49:08,107
[speaks African language]

684
00:49:36,135 --> 00:49:39,762
[leopard hissing]

685
00:50:00,533 --> 00:50:04,662
COME, BROTHER.
COME, COME, COME.

686
00:50:15,339 --> 00:50:18,301
- MR. VARTY?

687
00:50:18,301 --> 00:50:19,969
- HELLO.

688
00:50:19,969 --> 00:50:22,305
- I’M LOOKING FOR MR. VARTY.

689
00:50:22,305 --> 00:50:23,473
- WELL, HE’S NOT HERE RIGHT NOW.

690
00:50:23,473 --> 00:50:26,226
BUT MAYBE I CAN HELP YOU.
I’M CHRISTINE SHAYE.

691
00:50:26,226 --> 00:50:29,896
- VAN HEERDEN.
WILDLIFE MANAGEMENT.

692
00:50:29,896 --> 00:50:32,440
WHERE IS VARTY?

693
00:50:32,440 --> 00:50:35,027
- I’M NOT SURE.

694
00:50:35,027 --> 00:50:36,861
CAN I MAKE YOU SOME TEA?

695
00:50:36,861 --> 00:50:40,240
- EH, NO THANKS.

696
00:50:40,240 --> 00:50:42,325
- YOU KNOW, HE MAY BE A WHILE.

697
00:50:42,325 --> 00:50:45,120
DO YOU WANT ME TO JUST TELL HIM
THAT YOU CAME BY?

698
00:50:45,120 --> 00:50:47,206
- IT’S NOT THAT SIMPLE.

699
00:50:47,206 --> 00:50:50,625
WHERE ARE THE CUBS?

700
00:50:50,625 --> 00:50:51,584
- THE CUBS?

701
00:50:51,584 --> 00:50:54,879
- YEAH, THE LEOPARD CUBS.

702
00:50:54,879 --> 00:50:56,422
- OH, THOSE CUBS.

703
00:50:56,422 --> 00:50:58,674
- WHAT OTHER CUBS?

704
00:50:58,674 --> 00:51:00,885
- ARE YOU SURE I CAN’T HELP YOU?

705
00:51:00,885 --> 00:51:03,055
- IT’S A VERY DELICATE MATTER.

706
00:51:03,055 --> 00:51:06,307
IT’S ABOUT THE PERMIT
APPLICATIONS.

707
00:51:09,727 --> 00:51:11,854
- YOU MEAN A PERMIT
FOR THE CUBS?

708
00:51:11,854 --> 00:51:15,025
- I THINK I BETTER WAIT
FOR MR. VARTY.

709
00:51:15,025 --> 00:51:17,194
THERE IS A BIG PROBLEM.

710
00:51:17,194 --> 00:51:18,736
- OH.

711
00:51:18,736 --> 00:51:21,240
- OH, THEN YOU
MUST HAVE NOT HEARD.

712
00:51:21,240 --> 00:51:23,283
- NOT HEARD WHAT?

713
00:51:23,283 --> 00:51:24,284
- IT WAS AWFUL.

714
00:51:24,284 --> 00:51:26,953
THEY, UH, THEY WERE KILLED.

715
00:51:26,953 --> 00:51:28,663
BY LIONS.

716
00:51:28,663 --> 00:51:30,165
- THE CUBS?

717
00:51:30,165 --> 00:51:32,292
- YEAH, BOTH OF THEM.

718
00:51:32,292 --> 00:51:35,461
OH, IT WAS JUST SO SAD.

719
00:51:35,461 --> 00:51:37,256
TRAGIC, REALLY.

720
00:51:37,256 --> 00:51:37,880
AND J.V.--

721
00:51:37,880 --> 00:51:40,842
OH, J.V.’S BEEN ACTING
SO STRANGE EVER SINCE.

722
00:51:40,842 --> 00:51:44,179
YOU KNOW, HE DISAPPEARS
SOMETIMES FOR DAYS.

723
00:51:44,179 --> 00:51:46,806
THAT’S WHERE HE IS NOW.

724
00:51:46,806 --> 00:51:47,557
JUST GONE.

725
00:51:47,557 --> 00:51:48,641
ELMON WENT TO GO LOOK FOR HIM.

726
00:51:48,641 --> 00:51:50,351
WE’RE BOTH VERY WORRIED
ABOUT HIM.

727
00:51:50,351 --> 00:51:54,064
- YEAH.
YEAH, YEAH, YEAH.

728
00:51:58,860 --> 00:52:00,403
EH.

729
00:52:00,403 --> 00:52:01,445
MEJUFFROUW SHAYE.

730
00:52:01,445 --> 00:52:05,825
I FIND YOUR STORY
VERY DIFFICULT TO BELIEVE.

731
00:52:05,825 --> 00:52:07,077
- OH, MR. HEERDEN--

732
00:52:07,077 --> 00:52:08,287
- VAN.
IT’S VAN HEERDEN

733
00:52:08,287 --> 00:52:13,666
- MR. VAN HEERDEN,
I WOULD NOT JOKE ABOUT THIS.

734
00:52:13,666 --> 00:52:17,461
HERE.

735
00:52:17,461 --> 00:52:19,006
- EH.

736
00:52:22,050 --> 00:52:24,802
WHEN DID YOU SAY THIS WAS?

737
00:52:24,802 --> 00:52:27,347
- UH, LAST WEEK.

738
00:52:27,347 --> 00:52:29,765
- UH.
[tsking]

739
00:52:29,765 --> 00:52:32,560
VERY SAD.

740
00:52:33,061 --> 00:52:34,104
AH, WELL.

741
00:52:34,104 --> 00:52:37,357
I’LL HAVE TO TAKE THIS
AS EVIDENCE, YOU KNOW.

742
00:52:37,357 --> 00:52:39,192
- YEAH, OF COURSE.

743
00:52:39,192 --> 00:52:39,859
- OH, WELL.

744
00:52:39,859 --> 00:52:43,863
SUPPOSE THERE’S NO NEED FOR ME
TO WAIT AROUND NO MORE.

745
00:52:43,863 --> 00:52:46,449
BUT YOU’LL HAVE TO COME IN
TO SIGN SOME FORMS.

746
00:52:46,449 --> 00:52:48,826
- SURE.
OKAY.

747
00:52:48,826 --> 00:52:50,411
- TELL MR. VARTY I WAS HERE.

748
00:52:50,411 --> 00:52:52,872
- I WILL.

749
00:52:55,083 --> 00:53:00,047
- YOU KNOW, I DID TELL HIM
IT WAS FOR THEIR OWN GOOD.

750
00:53:00,047 --> 00:53:01,964
- I KNOW.

751
00:53:01,964 --> 00:53:03,424
WELL, IT WAS NICE MEETING YOU.

752
00:53:03,424 --> 00:53:06,053
- BYE, MISS SHAYE.

753
00:53:09,430 --> 00:53:12,017
- [whispering]
J.V.

754
00:53:15,062 --> 00:53:16,104
J.V.!

755
00:53:16,104 --> 00:53:16,604
- YEAH?

756
00:53:16,604 --> 00:53:18,481
- A GUY WAS JUST HERE
ABOUT A PERMIT.

757
00:53:18,481 --> 00:53:20,566
I THINK HE WANTED
TO TAKE THE CUBS.

758
00:53:20,566 --> 00:53:21,776
- VAN HEERDEN?

759
00:53:21,776 --> 00:53:22,652
- YEAH.

760
00:53:22,652 --> 00:53:23,611
- WHAT DID YOU SAY?

761
00:53:23,611 --> 00:53:26,073
- I SHOWED HIM PICTURES
OF THE DEAD CUBS.

762
00:53:26,073 --> 00:53:28,408
- THINK HE BELIEVED YOU?

763
00:53:28,408 --> 00:53:29,409
- I MAY HAVE STALLED HIM,

764
00:53:29,409 --> 00:53:31,535
BUT I DON’T KNOW
IF HE WAS CONVINCED.

765
00:53:31,535 --> 00:53:33,663
- "DEAR MR. NGLOVO,

766
00:53:33,663 --> 00:53:35,456
"I AM LOOKING FOR A LOCATION

767
00:53:35,456 --> 00:53:40,003
"TO RELEASE
MY TWO HAND-RAISED LEOPARD CUBS,

768
00:53:40,003 --> 00:53:46,634
"AND I BELIEVE THE SIZE
AND REMOTENESS OF YOUR PARK

769
00:53:46,634 --> 00:53:50,554
"WILL MAKE IT
AN IDEAL DESTINATION.

770
00:53:50,554 --> 00:53:51,806
"AS TIME IS OF THE ESSENCE,

771
00:53:51,806 --> 00:53:54,059
PLEASE COULD YOU REPLY
IMMEDIATELY..."

772
00:53:54,059 --> 00:53:54,934
- "DEAR MRS. SAMUELS,

773
00:53:54,934 --> 00:53:56,560
"I’VE BEEN MOST PRIVILEGED
TO BE PART

774
00:53:56,560 --> 00:53:59,022
"OF A VERY SPECIAL PROJECT
OF HAND-RAISING

775
00:53:59,022 --> 00:54:00,815
"TWO OF THE CUTEST ORPHAN
LEOPARD CUBS

776
00:54:00,815 --> 00:54:03,068
"AFTER THEIR MOTHER
WAS KILLED BY LIONS.

777
00:54:03,068 --> 00:54:06,071
"WE NOW NEED TO FIND THEM
A NEW HOME IN A WILDERNESS

778
00:54:06,071 --> 00:54:08,448
"WHERE THEY WILL NOT BE
THREATENED BY POACHERS.

779
00:54:08,448 --> 00:54:10,242
"THEY SIMPLY CANNOT BE PUT
IN A ZOO,

780
00:54:10,242 --> 00:54:12,576
"AND I UNDERSTAND YOU HAVE
A FARM LARGE ENOUGH

781
00:54:12,576 --> 00:54:13,577
TO ALLOW THEM TO ROAM FREE."

782
00:54:13,577 --> 00:54:17,040
- "I UNDERSTAND YOU STILL HAVE
NO MAJOR PREDATORS

783
00:54:17,040 --> 00:54:20,210
"AND WAS HOPING TO INTEREST YOU
IN THE RELEASE..."

784
00:54:20,210 --> 00:54:21,294
- BYE, TIDI.
- BYE!

785
00:54:21,294 --> 00:54:25,424
- "OF TWO YOUNG LEOPARDS
INTO YOUR RESERVE."

786
00:54:33,514 --> 00:54:36,351
- [speaks African language]

787
00:54:37,019 --> 00:54:40,688
[drumming and chanting]

788
00:54:58,040 --> 00:55:00,708
[speaking African language]

789
00:55:11,094 --> 00:55:12,220
- YO.

790
00:55:12,220 --> 00:55:13,013
- MENEER STEVENS.

791
00:55:13,013 --> 00:55:15,098
- SO WHAT’S HAPPENING
WITH THE CUBS?

792
00:55:15,098 --> 00:55:18,726
- UH, THERE IS A PROBLEM.

793
00:55:18,726 --> 00:55:23,814
- I PAY YOU $10,000,
YOU TELL ME YOU GOT A PROBLEM?

794
00:55:23,814 --> 00:55:25,150
- THE CUBS ARE DEAD.

795
00:55:25,150 --> 00:55:26,734
- THE CUBS ARE D--

796
00:55:26,734 --> 00:55:28,736
THE CUBS ARE WHAT?

797
00:55:28,736 --> 00:55:31,281
- THEY WERE KILLED BY LIONS.

798
00:55:31,281 --> 00:55:33,741
HERE, TAKE A LOOK FOR YOURSELF.

799
00:55:33,741 --> 00:55:34,867
WHAT DO YOU WANT ME TO DO,

800
00:55:34,867 --> 00:55:38,497
DIG UP THEIR BONES
AND BRING THEM TO YOU?

801
00:55:42,958 --> 00:55:47,047
- WHO YOU TRYING TO BULLSHIT,
EH?

802
00:55:47,047 --> 00:55:48,090
LOOK HERE.

803
00:55:48,090 --> 00:55:49,549
THIS CUB DIED OF MANGE.

804
00:55:49,549 --> 00:55:51,051
AND THIS ONE HERE,

805
00:55:51,051 --> 00:55:53,053
THIS IS A SUB-ADULT;
LOOK AT THE CANINES.

806
00:55:53,053 --> 00:55:54,262
THESE AREN’T VARTY’S CUBS.

807
00:55:54,262 --> 00:55:58,641
WHO YOU TRYING TO CON, PAL?

808
00:55:58,641 --> 00:56:00,810
- ACH.

809
00:56:00,810 --> 00:56:02,062
THAT WOMAN...

810
00:56:02,062 --> 00:56:06,066
YEAH, YOU HAVE STILL GOT
YOURSELF A DEAL.

811
00:56:06,066 --> 00:56:09,735
- YOU BETTER BELIEVE IT.

812
00:56:13,697 --> 00:56:16,700
[projector whirring]

813
00:56:16,700 --> 00:56:17,660
- OH, THIS IS GREAT.

814
00:56:17,660 --> 00:56:20,163
WE CAN PUT THIS IN
WITH INSTINCTIVE BEHAVIOR

815
00:56:20,163 --> 00:56:23,707
BECAUSE IT DEALS WITH BALANCE
AND LOWER CENTER OF GRAVITY.

816
00:56:23,707 --> 00:56:26,044
- WE COULD DO A COMPARISON HERE
WITH LION.

817
00:56:26,044 --> 00:56:26,710
- OH, YEAH.

818
00:56:26,710 --> 00:56:29,589
- SHOW THAT THEY ALSO
USED BE A TREE-CLIMBING CAT,

819
00:56:29,589 --> 00:56:31,091
AND THEN
AS THE SAVANNAHS DEVELOPED,

820
00:56:31,091 --> 00:56:33,135
THEY WENT OUT
INTO THE GRASSLANDS.

821
00:56:33,135 --> 00:56:34,844
LOOK AT HIM LAY HIS EARS BACK.

822
00:56:34,844 --> 00:56:35,803
- OH, YES.

823
00:56:35,803 --> 00:56:39,432
LOOK, HE’S A BIG BOY,
ISN’T HE?

824
00:56:39,432 --> 00:56:41,809
OH.

825
00:56:41,809 --> 00:56:43,936
- AH, IS ONE OF YOUR SHOTS.

826
00:56:43,936 --> 00:56:44,521
- SEE?

827
00:56:44,521 --> 00:56:46,939
- SEE, I’M IMPRESSED.
- THANK YOU.

828
00:56:46,939 --> 00:56:48,024
- NOT BAD AT ALL.

829
00:56:48,024 --> 00:56:49,650
- LOOK AT HIM.

830
00:56:49,650 --> 00:56:51,194
YOU LIKE IT TOO, HUH?

831
00:56:51,194 --> 00:56:52,653
WHO IS THAT UP THERE?

832
00:56:52,653 --> 00:56:55,948
WHO IS THAT?
HUH?

833
00:56:58,451 --> 00:57:00,828
YEAH, GO GET HIM.
YOU GO GET HIM.

834
00:57:00,828 --> 00:57:02,122
YOU GO GET HIM.

835
00:57:02,122 --> 00:57:03,498
- AH.

836
00:57:03,498 --> 00:57:04,665
- OH, IT’S GREAT.

837
00:57:04,665 --> 00:57:09,462
OH, THIS IS GONNA CUT TOGETHER
REALLY WELL.

838
00:57:09,462 --> 00:57:10,796
- [shouts]

839
00:57:10,796 --> 00:57:11,506
- OH!

840
00:57:11,506 --> 00:57:12,798
- THROW ME A DUVET!

841
00:57:12,798 --> 00:57:15,260
PULL THAT TABLE BACK!

842
00:57:15,260 --> 00:57:18,430
- GET AWAY FROM THERE!

843
00:57:18,430 --> 00:57:21,974
- PULL THE TABLE BACK.

844
00:57:21,974 --> 00:57:23,101
[leopard yowling]

845
00:57:23,101 --> 00:57:26,271
- LITTLE BOY, MOVE.

846
00:57:29,024 --> 00:57:31,109
THE CUBS.

847
00:57:31,109 --> 00:57:32,152
- CHECK THE COUNTER.

848
00:57:32,152 --> 00:57:34,154
- THEY’RE GONE.
IT’S SPREADING, J.V.

849
00:57:34,154 --> 00:57:35,905
- THROW THAT STUFF OUT THE
WINDOW.

850
00:57:35,905 --> 00:57:37,490
- GET THE NEGATIVE, J.V.

851
00:57:37,490 --> 00:57:39,034
- GO, GO, GO, GO!

852
00:57:39,034 --> 00:57:43,871
- GET THE NEGATIVE!

853
00:57:43,871 --> 00:57:45,540
J.V.!
COME ON!

854
00:57:45,540 --> 00:57:46,749
- I’M GONNA GET SOME MORE NEG.

855
00:57:46,749 --> 00:57:48,959
- J.V., FORGET THE NEGATIVE.
COME ON!

856
00:57:48,959 --> 00:57:49,835
- OKAY, GO TO THE CUB.

857
00:57:49,835 --> 00:57:52,589
- IT’S NO USE, J.V.
COME ON!

858
00:57:52,589 --> 00:57:54,840
COME ON!

859
00:58:15,778 --> 00:58:19,074
[drumming and chanting]

860
00:58:19,074 --> 00:58:27,457
♪ ♪

861
00:59:37,527 --> 00:59:38,944
- YEAH.

862
00:59:38,944 --> 00:59:42,407
[coughing]

863
00:59:46,910 --> 00:59:49,289
YEAH.

864
01:00:05,055 --> 01:00:08,683
[thunder rumbling]

865
01:00:49,724 --> 01:00:51,851
- HI, THERE.
- HI.

866
01:00:51,851 --> 01:00:53,019
ANY LUCK?
- I DON’T KNOW.

867
01:00:53,019 --> 01:00:56,856
I THINK WE’VE LOST MOST
OF THE MOTHER LEOPARD FOOTAGE.

868
01:00:56,856 --> 01:00:59,275
- TAKE A LOOK AT THIS.

869
01:01:01,236 --> 01:01:02,821
- "DEAR MR. ’VATY,’

870
01:01:02,821 --> 01:01:05,615
"YOUR LETTER I HAVE BEEN
RECEIVED YESTERDAY.

871
01:01:05,615 --> 01:01:08,909
"ME, I AM TELLING YOU
ABOUT THE MOST TERRIBLE DROUGHT

872
01:01:08,909 --> 01:01:12,205
"AFFECTING MY PEOPLE NOW.

873
01:01:12,205 --> 01:01:17,627
"DANGEROUS LIONS THERE ARE
RAVAGING MY CATTLE.

874
01:01:17,627 --> 01:01:22,090
"SO YOU NOW BELIEVING YOU,
MY FRIEND.

875
01:01:22,090 --> 01:01:23,299
"IT IS QUITE IMPOSSIBLE

876
01:01:23,299 --> 01:01:26,761
TO RELEASE YOUR LEOPARDS
AT THIS TIME."

877
01:01:26,761 --> 01:01:27,303
OH, J.V.

878
01:01:27,303 --> 01:01:29,180
I HAD NO IDEA
IT’D BE SO DIFFICULT.

879
01:01:29,180 --> 01:01:30,890
WHAT ARE WE GONNA DO?

880
01:01:30,890 --> 01:01:33,768
- UH, WE GOT TO TRY KENYA.

881
01:01:33,768 --> 01:01:36,813
IT’S OUR ONLY HOPE.

882
01:01:46,281 --> 01:01:48,783
- [speaks African language]

883
01:01:50,160 --> 01:01:53,788
[people murmuring]

884
01:02:02,963 --> 01:02:06,759
[speaks African language]

885
01:02:13,224 --> 01:02:15,226
ARE YOU LESTER?

886
01:02:15,226 --> 01:02:17,729
[speaks African language]

887
01:02:17,729 --> 01:02:18,730
- HUH?

888
01:02:18,730 --> 01:02:19,272
VARTY?

889
01:02:19,272 --> 01:02:21,232
- DO YOU KNOW WHERE
VARTY’S CAMP IS?

890
01:02:21,232 --> 01:02:22,066
- WHO’S LOOKING?

891
01:02:22,066 --> 01:02:23,818
- DO YOU KNOW WHERE IT IS, MAN?

892
01:02:23,818 --> 01:02:26,070
- UH, MAYBE.

893
01:02:26,070 --> 01:02:28,448
- EH.

894
01:02:30,575 --> 01:02:34,287
WE’LL BE NEEDING A GUIDE.
HERE.

895
01:02:34,287 --> 01:02:36,581
- IT IS FAR.

896
01:02:36,581 --> 01:02:39,501
- YEAH.

897
01:02:39,501 --> 01:02:41,461
- MY JEEP IS OLD.

898
01:02:41,461 --> 01:02:44,714
’63.

899
01:02:44,714 --> 01:02:46,716
- EH.

900
01:02:46,716 --> 01:02:51,304
- TIRES, OIL.

901
01:02:51,679 --> 01:02:53,848
OTHER HALF LATER.

902
01:03:40,478 --> 01:03:43,982
[lion snarling]

903
01:03:46,734 --> 01:03:49,070
- UH-OH.

904
01:03:57,120 --> 01:03:59,747
GO AWAY! GO!

905
01:04:02,834 --> 01:04:05,753
LEAVE ME ALONE!

906
01:04:05,753 --> 01:04:08,089
GO AWAY!

907
01:04:11,801 --> 01:04:13,845
LEAVE THE BIKE ALONE!

908
01:04:13,845 --> 01:04:14,846
LEAVE IT!

909
01:04:14,846 --> 01:04:16,764
DON’T BREAK IT!

910
01:04:16,764 --> 01:04:18,017
PLEASE!

911
01:04:18,017 --> 01:04:20,060
[air hissing]

912
01:04:20,060 --> 01:04:22,937
OH, LOOK WHAT YOU’VE DONE.

913
01:04:30,111 --> 01:04:34,074
LESTER!
LESTER!

914
01:04:34,074 --> 01:04:36,534
COME BACK!

915
01:04:39,120 --> 01:04:41,581
[sniffles]

916
01:04:59,265 --> 01:05:00,308
- YEAH?

917
01:05:00,308 --> 01:05:02,602
- YEAH.
NOT SO FAR.

918
01:05:02,602 --> 01:05:07,565
UH, OTHER HALF.

919
01:05:07,565 --> 01:05:09,150
THIS WAY.

920
01:05:09,150 --> 01:05:12,071
- [speaks African language]

921
01:05:19,786 --> 01:05:23,665
- [speaking African language]

922
01:05:28,753 --> 01:05:32,091
- I CAN ONLY IMAGINE
WHAT YOU TWO ARE TALKING ABOUT.

923
01:05:32,091 --> 01:05:33,050
I DON’T WANT TO HEAR IT.

924
01:05:33,050 --> 01:05:36,344
TONIGHT YOU ARE
EATING VEGETABLES.

925
01:05:36,344 --> 01:05:39,972
[animals calling]

926
01:05:54,113 --> 01:05:56,073
- LESTER!

927
01:05:56,073 --> 01:05:58,366
TAKE ME TO VARTY’S CAMP!

928
01:05:58,366 --> 01:06:01,369
WE’RE GOING TO GET THOSE CATS!

929
01:06:01,369 --> 01:06:03,204
BRING THE CAGES!

930
01:06:03,204 --> 01:06:05,748
CALL THE ZOO!

931
01:06:19,762 --> 01:06:20,471
- ELMON.

932
01:06:20,471 --> 01:06:22,015
[speaking African language]

933
01:06:22,015 --> 01:06:24,350
- [laughs]

934
01:06:30,606 --> 01:06:33,026
- WELL, I’M GONNA GO TO BED.

935
01:06:33,026 --> 01:06:34,235
GOOD NIGHT.

936
01:06:34,235 --> 01:06:35,445
- GOOD NIGHT.

937
01:06:35,445 --> 01:06:37,905
- NIGHT.

938
01:06:44,829 --> 01:06:46,289
- YEAH.

939
01:06:46,289 --> 01:06:47,373
- YEAH, WHERE?

940
01:06:47,373 --> 01:06:48,083
QUIETLY, NOW.

941
01:06:48,083 --> 01:06:51,919
WE MUST FIRST SEE WHERE
HE’S KEEPING THE CUBS.

942
01:07:06,059 --> 01:07:09,562
[animal noises]

943
01:07:15,818 --> 01:07:19,363
[owl hooting]

944
01:07:19,697 --> 01:07:22,909
- [whispers]
WHAT’S THAT, LITTLE BOY?

945
01:07:27,789 --> 01:07:31,210
- [chuckling]

946
01:07:31,210 --> 01:07:32,002
- LESTER.

947
01:07:32,002 --> 01:07:34,213
LESTER!
- HE’S GONE.

948
01:07:34,213 --> 01:07:34,962
- AH!

949
01:07:34,962 --> 01:07:37,632
PUT YOUR TORCH OUT.

950
01:07:53,273 --> 01:07:54,816
ARE YOU READY?
- NO.

951
01:07:54,816 --> 01:07:56,818
GOT A PROBLEM.

952
01:07:56,818 --> 01:07:57,944
- [yowls]

953
01:07:57,944 --> 01:07:58,903
- WHO’S THERE?

954
01:07:58,903 --> 01:08:00,197
HEY, WHO’S THERE?

955
01:08:00,197 --> 01:08:01,489
- SORRY, BOSS.

956
01:08:01,489 --> 01:08:03,033
[speaking African language]

957
01:08:03,033 --> 01:08:03,991
- SOMEONE’S OUT THERE.

958
01:08:03,991 --> 01:08:05,743
COME ON, LET’S GO!
GO, GO, GO!

959
01:08:05,743 --> 01:08:08,371
- HEY, LET’S GO.
RUN!

960
01:08:08,371 --> 01:08:10,290
[gunshots]
- EH, COME BACK!

961
01:08:10,290 --> 01:08:11,916
GET BACK HERE, YOU COWARDS!

962
01:08:11,916 --> 01:08:13,252
- WE’RE GONNA GET CAUGHT!
RUN!

963
01:08:13,252 --> 01:08:15,336
- HOLD YOUR FIRE!
STOP SHOOTING!

964
01:08:15,336 --> 01:08:17,880
HOLD YOUR FIRE!

965
01:08:17,880 --> 01:08:18,798
VAN HEERDEN?

966
01:08:18,798 --> 01:08:21,301
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

967
01:08:21,301 --> 01:08:23,053
- ANTI-POACHING.

968
01:08:23,053 --> 01:08:25,555
- YEAH.
[chuckles]

969
01:08:25,555 --> 01:08:27,890
"TAKE ME TO VARTY’S CAMP."

970
01:08:27,890 --> 01:08:30,434
[giggles]

971
01:08:30,434 --> 01:08:31,311
- [grunts]

972
01:08:31,311 --> 01:08:37,067
- LESTER,
YOU DOUBLE-CROSSING BASTARD.

973
01:08:37,067 --> 01:08:39,735
[groans]

974
01:08:39,735 --> 01:08:42,239
- WHAT HAPPENED?

975
01:09:02,259 --> 01:09:03,343
- HEY, LESTER.

976
01:09:03,343 --> 01:09:04,011
- HEY, TIDI!

977
01:09:04,011 --> 01:09:05,928
WHAT ARE YOU DOING
ALL THE WAY OUT HERE?

978
01:09:05,928 --> 01:09:06,971
- THERE WAS A LION YESTERDAY.

979
01:09:06,971 --> 01:09:08,431
- DOES YOUR MOTHER KNOW
YOU’RE HERE?

980
01:09:08,431 --> 01:09:10,267
- I HAD TO SLEEP
IN THE TREE ALL NIGHT.

981
01:09:10,267 --> 01:09:12,560
AND YOU DRIVE PAST ME.

982
01:09:17,607 --> 01:09:20,943
- "DEAR MR. WALKER..."

983
01:09:34,916 --> 01:09:36,542
- THEY’RE COMING
TO TAKE THE CUBS!

984
01:09:36,542 --> 01:09:38,211
- J.V., VAN HEERDEN’S COMING!

985
01:09:38,211 --> 01:09:39,462
- VAN HEERDEN!
HE’S COMING!

986
01:09:39,462 --> 01:09:41,256
HE’S COMING WITH THE CAGES
TO TAKE THE CUBS.

987
01:09:41,256 --> 01:09:44,134
I SENT HIM THE WRONG WAY,
BUT HE’LL FIND US.

988
01:09:44,134 --> 01:09:45,218
WE MUST GET OUT OF HERE.

989
01:09:45,218 --> 01:09:46,969
HE’S REALLY SERIOUS THIS TIME.

990
01:09:46,969 --> 01:09:49,389
- JUST TAKE WHAT YOU NEED.
- COME.

991
01:09:52,892 --> 01:09:55,603
- THAT WAY!

992
01:09:55,603 --> 01:09:57,272
- OKAY, PRETTY.

993
01:09:57,272 --> 01:09:58,856
- OKAY.

994
01:09:58,856 --> 01:10:00,608
- GOOD BOY, GOOD BOY.

995
01:10:00,608 --> 01:10:02,818
THERE YOU GUYS GO.

996
01:10:13,246 --> 01:10:15,332
- OKAY.

997
01:10:15,332 --> 01:10:17,792
[grunting]

998
01:10:29,762 --> 01:10:34,976
- J.V., WAIT.
WAIT, WAIT, HANG ON.

999
01:10:34,976 --> 01:10:37,145
- THERE.

1000
01:10:46,487 --> 01:10:48,864
THAT’S THEIR CAMP.

1001
01:10:48,864 --> 01:10:52,244
THEY’RE GONE.

1002
01:10:52,244 --> 01:10:53,120
LET’S GO.

1003
01:10:53,120 --> 01:10:56,039
THEY COULDN’T HAVE GONE FAR.

1004
01:10:58,250 --> 01:11:00,335
FOLLOW THAT ROAD.

1005
01:11:00,335 --> 01:11:01,544
- WHAT ARE WE DOING THIS FOR?

1006
01:11:01,544 --> 01:11:03,046
- VARTY’S SMUGGLING ANIMALS.

1007
01:11:03,046 --> 01:11:05,298
HE MUST BE STOPPED.

1008
01:11:09,136 --> 01:11:11,096
B.J., B.J.,
DO YOU COPY?

1009
01:11:11,096 --> 01:11:12,472
WHAT IS YOUR LOCATION?

1010
01:11:12,472 --> 01:11:16,393
- I’M ON THE ROAD JUST SOUTH,
OVER.

1011
01:11:16,393 --> 01:11:18,186
- COPY YOU.

1012
01:11:21,231 --> 01:11:21,897
UP!

1013
01:11:21,897 --> 01:11:26,028
LET’S GET A BETTER VIEW
OF THE ROADS.

1014
01:11:28,821 --> 01:11:30,698
THERE’S VARTY.

1015
01:11:30,698 --> 01:11:31,615
VARTY.

1016
01:11:31,615 --> 01:11:32,700
FOLLOW HIM.

1017
01:11:32,700 --> 01:11:35,661
B.J., B.J.,
I’VE GOT VARTY.

1018
01:11:35,661 --> 01:11:37,872
- COPY.
WHAT’S HIS LOCATION?

1019
01:11:37,872 --> 01:11:41,460
- FOLLOW THE ROAD TO BIG DAM.
INTERCEPT HIM!

1020
01:12:31,551 --> 01:12:34,221
OKAY, WE’VE GOT HIM!

1021
01:12:34,221 --> 01:12:37,057
LET’S TAKE ’ER DOWN.

1022
01:12:48,609 --> 01:12:52,531
NO LUCK, MR. VARTY.

1023
01:12:52,531 --> 01:12:54,032
- HELLO.

1024
01:12:54,032 --> 01:12:55,242
- OH, YOU.

1025
01:12:55,242 --> 01:12:56,826
WHERE IS VARTY?

1026
01:12:56,826 --> 01:12:57,910
- VARTY?

1027
01:12:57,910 --> 01:12:59,079
OH, YOU MEAN J.V.

1028
01:12:59,079 --> 01:13:00,996
YOU KNOW, I DON’T KNOW.

1029
01:13:00,996 --> 01:13:02,957
HE JUST TOOK OFF AGAIN.

1030
01:13:02,957 --> 01:13:04,084
BUT DON’T WORRY.

1031
01:13:04,084 --> 01:13:06,086
HE’S GOT ELMON WITH HIM.

1032
01:13:06,086 --> 01:13:08,963
AND THE CUBS.

1033
01:13:08,963 --> 01:13:09,755
- [giggling]

1034
01:13:09,755 --> 01:13:11,508
- LESTER.
HEY.

1035
01:13:11,508 --> 01:13:12,384
LESTER.
- YEAH?

1036
01:13:12,384 --> 01:13:13,634
- YOU THINK YOU’RE CLEVER, EH?

1037
01:13:13,634 --> 01:13:14,718
- AH, IT’S A MISTAKE, MAN.

1038
01:13:14,718 --> 01:13:15,886
LOOK, NO ONE’S PERFECT, EH?

1039
01:13:15,886 --> 01:13:18,889
- DO YOU THINK YOU CAN MAKE
A FOOL OUT OF ME?

1040
01:13:18,889 --> 01:13:20,392
- [stammers]

1041
01:13:20,392 --> 01:13:23,853
- WHERE?

1042
01:13:23,853 --> 01:13:27,190
- [chuckles]

1043
01:13:27,190 --> 01:13:28,441
B.J.!

1044
01:13:28,441 --> 01:13:29,484
AIRSTRIP!

1045
01:13:29,484 --> 01:13:32,237
- OKAY!
LET’S GET HIM!

1046
01:13:32,237 --> 01:13:33,821
- SORRY.

1047
01:13:34,573 --> 01:13:37,534
- AIRSTRIP.
LET’S GO!

1048
01:13:51,131 --> 01:13:54,842
- [speaking African language]

1049
01:13:56,760 --> 01:14:00,182
[all speaking African language]

1050
01:14:13,111 --> 01:14:16,448
- [speaks African language]
- OKAY.

1051
01:14:25,998 --> 01:14:26,583
J.V.!

1052
01:14:26,583 --> 01:14:27,584
- YEAH?
- HELICOPTER.

1053
01:14:27,584 --> 01:14:29,169
HELICOPTER,
[speaks African language]

1054
01:14:29,169 --> 01:14:31,837
- [speaks African language]
LET’S GO!

1055
01:14:37,219 --> 01:14:40,763
[engine roars]

1056
01:14:41,473 --> 01:14:44,142
FOX NOVEMBER VICTOR,
THIS IS...

1057
01:14:44,142 --> 01:14:46,102
[engine rumbling]

1058
01:14:46,102 --> 01:14:47,020
- QUICKLY!

1059
01:14:47,020 --> 01:14:50,565
DON’T LET THEM GET AWAY!

1060
01:14:59,032 --> 01:15:02,118
FASTER, MAN,
GET IN FRONT OF HIM!

1061
01:15:03,495 --> 01:15:06,206
IN FRONT OF HIM!

1062
01:15:08,541 --> 01:15:10,043
BLOCK HIM OFF!

1063
01:15:10,043 --> 01:15:11,002
BLOCK HIM!

1064
01:15:11,002 --> 01:15:11,835
- ARE YOU CRAZY?

1065
01:15:11,835 --> 01:15:12,671
FORGET IT, VAN HEERDEN.

1066
01:15:12,671 --> 01:15:14,506
THIS IS NOT HOW WE OPERATE.
- COME ON!

1067
01:15:14,506 --> 01:15:15,839
AFTER HIM!
BLOCK HIM OFF, MAN!

1068
01:15:15,839 --> 01:15:19,636
- I’M NOT GONNA BE PART
OF THIS CIRCUS.

1069
01:15:22,514 --> 01:15:25,600
- UGH!

1070
01:15:28,520 --> 01:15:31,897
- [speaking African language]

1071
01:15:31,897 --> 01:15:34,817
[both laugh]

1072
01:15:39,656 --> 01:15:43,201
[all cheering]

1073
01:16:42,469 --> 01:16:45,805
[African choral music]

1074
01:16:45,805 --> 01:16:54,189
♪ ♪

1075
01:17:31,768 --> 01:17:35,647
- [speaking African language]

1076
01:17:40,235 --> 01:17:44,072
[all speaking African language]

1077
01:17:46,157 --> 01:17:47,742
- RUN THAT BY ME AGAIN, PLEASE.

1078
01:17:47,742 --> 01:17:51,079
WE’VE LOST 60%
OF THE ORIGINAL NEGATIVE?

1079
01:17:51,079 --> 01:17:51,788
- IN A FIRE.

1080
01:17:51,788 --> 01:17:53,456
ONE OF THE CUBS KNOCKED OVER
A PARAFFIN LAMP.

1081
01:17:53,456 --> 01:17:56,917
- AND PLUS THIS $9,000 INVOICE
FOR THE PLANE?

1082
01:17:56,917 --> 01:17:58,461
I THOUGHT THAT WAS FOR AERIALS.

1083
01:17:58,461 --> 01:17:59,421
- THERE WAS NO OTHER WAY.

1084
01:17:59,421 --> 01:18:00,921
THE CUBS WERE BEING TAKEN OFF
TO A ZOO.

1085
01:18:00,921 --> 01:18:04,384
I WAS TRYING TO SAVE THEM
AND THE PROJECT.

1086
01:18:04,384 --> 01:18:06,136
- HERE WE GO AGAIN.

1087
01:18:06,136 --> 01:18:08,263
- DAN, PLEASE DON’T
SHUT THIS DOWN.

1088
01:18:08,263 --> 01:18:09,681
- I’M VERY SORRY, CHRISTINE,

1089
01:18:09,681 --> 01:18:11,307
BUT THIS HAS GONE FAR ENOUGH.

1090
01:18:11,307 --> 01:18:12,392
- JUDITH, COME IN HERE, PLEASE.

1091
01:18:12,392 --> 01:18:15,103
- I CAN SALVAGE THIS PROJECT.
PLEASE.

1092
01:18:15,103 --> 01:18:16,271
I DON’T WANT TO GIVE UP ON IT.

1093
01:18:16,271 --> 01:18:19,441
- I TOLD YOU
THIS VARTY CHARACTER

1094
01:18:19,441 --> 01:18:20,900
WAS A GODDAMN WALKING DISASTER.

1095
01:18:20,900 --> 01:18:22,610
- IT’S MORE THAN JUST A FILM,
JACK.

1096
01:18:22,610 --> 01:18:25,113
WE’RE TALKING
ABOUT THEIR SURVIVAL.

1097
01:18:25,113 --> 01:18:26,739
- OH, PLEASE.

1098
01:18:26,739 --> 01:18:30,076
- DAN, DON’T SHUT ME DOWN.

1099
01:18:32,579 --> 01:18:36,124
- YES, JUDITH, I WANT YOU
TO PREPARE AN INSURANCE CLAIM

1100
01:18:36,124 --> 01:18:37,792
ON THE LEOPARD FILM.

1101
01:18:37,792 --> 01:18:38,585
- INSURANCE CLAIM?

1102
01:18:38,585 --> 01:18:41,254
WE’VE GOT ENOUGH GROUNDS
FOR A LAWSUIT AGAINST THIS GUY.

1103
01:18:41,254 --> 01:18:42,839
- PLEASE, JACK.

1104
01:18:42,839 --> 01:18:44,299
JUST STAY OUT OF THIS.

1105
01:18:44,299 --> 01:18:46,551
CHRISTINE WILL GIVE YOU
ALL THE DETAILS.

1106
01:18:46,551 --> 01:18:49,012
THANK YOU.

1107
01:18:55,976 --> 01:18:57,479
- "DEAR CHRISTINE.

1108
01:18:57,479 --> 01:18:59,647
"I’VE SAFELY LANDED
IN THE MASAI MARA,

1109
01:18:59,647 --> 01:19:02,442
"WHERE WE HAVE BEEN WELCOMED
WITH OPEN ARMS.

1110
01:19:02,442 --> 01:19:06,154
"THIS AREA IS A VAST EXPANSE
OF OPEN SPACES

1111
01:19:06,154 --> 01:19:07,197
"TEEMING WITH GAME,

1112
01:19:07,197 --> 01:19:10,408
"ONE OF AFRICA’S LAST GREAT
WILDERNESSES.

1113
01:19:10,408 --> 01:19:13,828
"YESTERDAY WE FILMED A HERD
OF 10,000 WILDEBEEST

1114
01:19:13,828 --> 01:19:17,499
"BRAVING THE CROCODILES
OF THE MARA RIVER.

1115
01:19:17,499 --> 01:19:19,125
"WISH YOU COULD HAVE BEEN HERE.

1116
01:19:19,125 --> 01:19:21,920
MISSING YOU,
J.V."

1117
01:20:08,716 --> 01:20:12,012
"WE’VE BEEN STAYING IN THE
MANIATTA WITH OUR MASAI FRIENDS

1118
01:20:12,012 --> 01:20:14,389
"AND ALL THEIR GOATS AND CATTLE.

1119
01:20:14,389 --> 01:20:15,807
"NOT EXACTLY THE RITZ,

1120
01:20:15,807 --> 01:20:17,517
"BUT THESE PROUD
AND HOSPITABLE PEOPLE

1121
01:20:17,517 --> 01:20:19,686
"STILL LIVE IN HARMONY
WITH THE ENVIRONMENT,

1122
01:20:19,686 --> 01:20:22,855
"SHARING THE LAND
WITH AFRICA’S WILDLIFE.

1123
01:20:22,855 --> 01:20:25,358
"THE CUBS HAVE BEEN
UP TO THEIR USUAL MISCHIEF.

1124
01:20:25,358 --> 01:20:27,360
"LITTLE GIRL IS
THE ONLY LEOPARD IN HISTORY

1125
01:20:27,360 --> 01:20:32,574
THAT HAS ATTACKED A MASAI GOAT
AND LIVED TO TELL THE TALE."

1126
01:20:42,375 --> 01:20:43,793
ELMON, WATCH THE GOAT!

1127
01:20:43,793 --> 01:20:44,335
- HEY!

1128
01:20:44,335 --> 01:20:48,214
[all shouting
in African language]

1129
01:20:53,761 --> 01:20:55,847
LEAVE THE GOAT, LITTLE GIRL!
LEAVE THE GOAT.

1130
01:20:55,847 --> 01:21:00,226
[men yelling and muttering
in African language]

1131
01:21:11,030 --> 01:21:12,031
- J.V.!

1132
01:21:12,031 --> 01:21:13,156
- SUPA.

1133
01:21:13,156 --> 01:21:16,743
- SUPA.
- [speaks African language]

1134
01:21:16,743 --> 01:21:20,538
[both speaking
African language]

1135
01:21:20,538 --> 01:21:21,873
- YEAH, IT’S FROM CHRISTINE.

1136
01:21:21,873 --> 01:21:23,083
- OH, GOOD.
- YEAH.

1137
01:21:23,083 --> 01:21:26,919
[speaking African language]

1138
01:21:36,471 --> 01:21:39,432
- J.V., WELL,
I HOPE THIS REACHES YOU.

1139
01:21:39,432 --> 01:21:42,143
OH, I WISH YOU COULD HAVE
SEEN VAN HEERDEN’S FACE

1140
01:21:42,143 --> 01:21:43,895
WHEN HE CAUGHT UP WITH ME.

1141
01:21:43,895 --> 01:21:47,899
I HATE TO DO THIS, BUT I SUPPOSE
I HAVE TO GIVE YOU THE BAD NEWS.

1142
01:21:47,899 --> 01:21:49,984
DAN HAS CANCELED THE PROJECT.

1143
01:21:49,984 --> 01:21:52,904
THERE WAS NOTHING I COULD SAY
TO CHANGE HIS MIND.

1144
01:21:52,904 --> 01:21:53,821
HE’S A BUSINESSMAN.

1145
01:21:53,821 --> 01:21:55,365
HE’S MAKING A BUSINESS DECISION.

1146
01:21:55,365 --> 01:21:57,034
I HAVE TO RESPECT IT.

1147
01:21:57,034 --> 01:22:00,495
I TRULY AM SORRY ABOUT HOW
EVERYTHING HAS TURNED OUT.

1148
01:22:00,495 --> 01:22:02,955
BUT LISTEN, I DO HAVE
A LITTLE MONEY ON MY OWN,

1149
01:22:02,955 --> 01:22:04,916
AND I’M TRYING MY BEST
TO DO SOMETHING

1150
01:22:04,916 --> 01:22:06,417
WITH THE MATERIAL WE HAVE LEFT.

1151
01:22:06,417 --> 01:22:08,003
I SENT YOU SOME MORE STOCK.

1152
01:22:08,003 --> 01:22:10,254
JUST HOPE YOUR OLD CAMERA
HOLDS OUT.

1153
01:22:10,254 --> 01:22:12,674
PLEASE LET ME KNOW IF
THERE’S ANYTHING ELSE YOU NEED.

1154
01:22:12,674 --> 01:22:17,261
THIS IS GOING TO BE DIFFICULT,
BUT I WILL NOT GIVE UP.

1155
01:22:17,261 --> 01:22:19,764
LOVE, CHRISTINE.

1156
01:22:24,560 --> 01:22:28,065
[birds chirping]

1157
01:22:30,191 --> 01:22:34,071
- [speaking African language]

1158
01:22:49,627 --> 01:22:53,506
- [speaking African language]

1159
01:23:35,757 --> 01:23:37,050
- "DEAR CHRISTINE,

1160
01:23:37,050 --> 01:23:39,635
"I HAVE TRAGIC NEWS
ABOUT LITTLE BOY.

1161
01:23:39,635 --> 01:23:42,055
"IT ALL HAPPENED SO FAST.

1162
01:23:42,055 --> 01:23:43,098
"THERE WAS NOTHING WE COULD DO.

1163
01:23:43,098 --> 01:23:44,640
"HE HAD WANDERED OFF,
AND YOU KNOW

1164
01:23:44,640 --> 01:23:47,602
"WHAT AN ADVENTUROUS SPIRIT
HE ALWAYS HAD.

1165
01:23:47,602 --> 01:23:49,270
IT IS DIFFICULT FOR ALL OF US."

1166
01:23:49,270 --> 01:23:51,647
- [crying]

1167
01:23:51,647 --> 01:23:55,485
[speaking African language]

1168
01:24:16,048 --> 01:24:18,549
- NO!

1169
01:24:18,549 --> 01:24:21,511
PRETTY BOY!

1170
01:24:27,683 --> 01:24:31,395
COME BACK, PRETTY BOY!

1171
01:24:39,570 --> 01:24:42,115
- [sniffling]

1172
01:25:02,468 --> 01:25:06,181
[all singing
in African language]

1173
01:25:06,181 --> 01:25:14,564
♪ ♪

1174
01:25:32,790 --> 01:25:35,376
- [speaking African language]

1175
01:25:35,376 --> 01:25:38,880
- "THE MASAI SAID HOW SORRY
THEY WERE ABOUT LITTLE BOY

1176
01:25:38,880 --> 01:25:41,924
"AND HOW THEY HAD RESPECTED
HIS COURAGE.

1177
01:25:41,924 --> 01:25:44,344
"BUT STILL, THEY ARE THE MASAI,

1178
01:25:44,344 --> 01:25:47,264
"THE GREAT CATTLEMEN
OF THE AFRICAN PLAINS,

1179
01:25:47,264 --> 01:25:51,310
"AND THEY MADE IT CLEAR THIS WAS
NO PLACE TO RELEASE LITTLE GIRL

1180
01:25:51,310 --> 01:25:54,645
AND THAT WE MUST TAKE HER
SOMEPLACE ELSE."

1181
01:25:57,648 --> 01:26:02,237
"THERE ARE SO FEW GREAT
OPEN SPACES LEFT IN AFRICA.

1182
01:26:02,237 --> 01:26:05,656
"THESE LAST WILDERNESS AREAS
ARE LIKE SHRINKING ISLANDS

1183
01:26:05,656 --> 01:26:08,492
"SURROUNDED BY A SEA
OF HUMANITY,

1184
01:26:08,492 --> 01:26:10,828
"AGRICULTURE, AND DEVELOPMENT.

1185
01:26:10,828 --> 01:26:15,917
"TO FIND THE REAL AFRICA,
UNDEVELOPED, UNSPOILT AND WILD,

1186
01:26:15,917 --> 01:26:18,794
"IS ALMOST IMPOSSIBLE.

1187
01:26:18,794 --> 01:26:19,879
"BUT THERE IS ONE PLACE,

1188
01:26:19,879 --> 01:26:24,800
"AND I HAVE BEEN GIVEN
PERMISSION TO RELEASE HER THERE.

1189
01:26:24,800 --> 01:26:25,593
"ZAMBIA.

1190
01:26:25,593 --> 01:26:28,846
"THIS IS OUR LAST CHANCE.

1191
01:26:41,068 --> 01:26:43,653
"THIS PLACE IS BETTER
THAN I EVER IMAGINED.

1192
01:26:43,653 --> 01:26:47,865
"IT FEELS LIKE WE ARE THE FIRST
PEOPLE TO WALK THIS LAND.

1193
01:26:47,865 --> 01:26:49,742
"THE GUARDIANS
OF THIS UNTAMED WILDERNESS

1194
01:26:49,742 --> 01:26:53,746
"ARE THE DEADLY TSETSE FLY
AND MALARIAL MOSQUITO.

1195
01:26:53,746 --> 01:26:54,789
"PEOPLE AND CATTLE,

1196
01:26:54,789 --> 01:26:58,126
"THE BIGGEST THREAT TO WILDLIFE
AND TO LITTLE GIRL,

1197
01:26:58,126 --> 01:27:00,628
CANNOT SURVIVE HERE."

1198
01:27:07,260 --> 01:27:10,763
[speaking African language]

1199
01:27:10,763 --> 01:27:14,142
OH, IT’S A SCORPION.

1200
01:27:14,142 --> 01:27:15,685
- [whistles]

1201
01:27:15,685 --> 01:27:18,521
[speaking African language]

1202
01:27:23,110 --> 01:27:24,027
- IT’S GONNA STING YOU.

1203
01:27:24,027 --> 01:27:25,903
- [speaks African language]

1204
01:27:25,903 --> 01:27:28,240
[laughs]

1205
01:27:28,240 --> 01:27:32,077
[speaking African language]

1206
01:27:47,967 --> 01:27:50,928
- "SHE IS NO LONGER
OUR LITTLE GIRL.

1207
01:27:50,928 --> 01:27:51,971
"WE CAN FEEL HER RESTLESSNESS.

1208
01:27:51,971 --> 01:27:56,393
"HER DESIRE FOR INDEPENDENCE
GROWS STRONGER EVERY DAY.

1209
01:27:56,393 --> 01:27:59,937
"SHE OFTEN WANDERS OFF ALONE,
EXPLORING HER NEW TERRITORY

1210
01:27:59,937 --> 01:28:06,111
AND SELDOM FOLLOWS US BACK
TO CAMP AFTER OUR LONG WALKS."

1211
01:28:13,576 --> 01:28:15,370
[sighs]

1212
01:28:24,628 --> 01:28:27,757
- [speaks African language]

1213
01:28:27,757 --> 01:28:30,385
- AH, SHE’S NOT
COMING BACK, ELMON.

1214
01:28:30,385 --> 01:28:31,677
SEE YOU TOMORROW.

1215
01:28:31,677 --> 01:28:33,055
- OKAY.

1216
01:28:33,055 --> 01:28:34,181
- SLEEP WELL.

1217
01:28:34,181 --> 01:28:36,141
- OKAY, SURE.

1218
01:28:41,645 --> 01:28:45,150
